  nickname: isa
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: f0e13320f8bc1254f8bca32b62d9305b, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Wickedness of Judah'
      title: The Wickedness of Judah
      number: 1
      content: The vision of Isaiah the son of Amoz, which he saw concerning Judah
        and Jerusalem in the days of Uzziah, Jotham, Ahaz, and Hezekiah, kings of
        Judah.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Hear, O heavens, and give ear, O earth!For the Lord has spoken:\u201CI
        have nourished and brought up children,And they have rebelled against Me;"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "The ox knows its ownerAnd the donkey its master\u2019s crib;But Israel
        does not know,My people do not consider.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Alas, sinful nation,A people laden with iniquity,A brood of evildoers,Children
        who are corrupters!They have forsaken the Lord,They have provoked to angerThe
        Holy One of Israel,They have turned away backward.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Why should you be stricken again?You will revolt more and more.The
        whole head is sick,And the whole heart faints.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: From the sole of the foot even to the head,There  is no soundness
        in it,But wounds and bruises and putrefying sores;They have not been closed
        or bound up,Or soothed with ointment.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Your country is desolate,Your cities are burned with fire;Strangers
        devour your land in your presence;And it  is desolate, as overthrown by strangers.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: So the daughter of Zion is left as a booth in a vineyard,As a hut
        in a garden of cucumbers,As a besieged city.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Unless the Lord of hostsHad left to us a very small remnant,We would
        have become like Sodom,We would have been made like Gomorrah.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Hear the word of the Lord,You rulers of Sodom;Give ear to the law
        of our God,You people of Gomorrah:'
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CTo what purpose is the multitude of your sacrifices to Me?\u201DSays
        the Lord.\u201CI have had enough of burnt offerings of ramsAnd the fat of
        fed cattle.I do not delight in the blood of bulls,Or of lambs or goats."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CWhen you come to appear before Me,Who has required this from
        your hand,To trample My courts?"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Bring no more futile sacrifices;Incense is an abomination to Me.The
        New Moons, the Sabbaths, and the calling of assemblies\u2014I cannot endure
        iniquity and the sacred meeting."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Your New Moons and your appointed feastsMy soul hates;They are a trouble
        to Me,I am weary of bearing them.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: When you spread out your hands,I will hide My eyes from you;Even though
        you make many prayers,I will not hear.Your hands are full of blood.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CWash yourselves, make yourselves clean;Put away the evil of
        your doings from before My eyes.Cease to do evil,"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Learn to do good;Seek justice,Rebuke the oppressor;Defend the fatherless,Plead
        for the widow.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CCome now, and let us reason together,\u201DSays the Lord,\u201CThough
        your sins are like scarlet,They shall be as white as snow;Though they are
        red like crimson,They shall be as wool."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: If you are willing and obedient,You shall eat the good of the land;
      comments: []
    - name: '20: The Degenerate City'
      title: The Degenerate City
      number: 20
      content: "But if you refuse and rebel,You shall be devoured by the sword\u201D;For
        the mouth of the Lord has spoken."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: How the faithful city has become a harlot!It was full of justice;Righteousness
        lodged in it,But now murderers.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Your silver has become dross,Your wine mixed with water.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Your princes are rebellious,And companions of thieves;Everyone loves
        bribes,And follows after rewards.They do not defend the fatherless,Nor does
        the cause of the widow come before them.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Therefore the Lord says,The Lord of hosts, the Mighty One of Israel,\u201CAh,
        I will rid Myself of My adversaries,And take vengeance on My enemies."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: I will turn My hand against you,And thoroughly purge away your dross,And
        take away all your alloy.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "I will restore your judges as at the first,And your counselors as
        at the beginning.Afterward you shall be called the city of righteousness,
        the faithful city.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Zion shall be redeemed with justice,And her penitents with righteousness.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: The destruction of transgressors and of sinners shall  be together,And
        those who forsake the Lord shall be consumed.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: For they shall be ashamed of the terebinth treesWhich you have desired;And
        you shall be embarrassed because of the gardensWhich you have chosen.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: For you shall be as a terebinth whose leaf fades,And as a garden that
        has no water.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: The strong shall be as tinder,And the work of it as a spark;Both will
        burn together,And no one shall quench them.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Future House of God'
      title: The Future House of God
      number: 1
      content: The word that Isaiah the son of Amoz saw concerning Judah and Jerusalem.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Now it shall come to pass in the latter daysThat the mountain of
        the Lord\u2019s houseShall be established on the top of the mountains,And
        shall be exalted above the hills;And all nations shall flow to it."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Many people shall come and say,\u201CCome, and let us go up to the
        mountain of the Lord,To the house of the God of Jacob;He will teach us His
        ways,And we shall walk in His paths.\u201DFor out of Zion shall go forth
        the law,And the word of the Lord from Jerusalem."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: The Day of the Lord'
      title: The Day of the Lord
      number: 4
      content: He shall judge between the nations,And rebuke many people;They shall
        beat their swords into plowshares,And their spears into pruning hooks;Nation
        shall not lift up sword against nation,Neither shall they learn war anymore.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: O house of Jacob, come and let us walkIn the light of the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: For You have forsaken Your people, the house of Jacob,Because they
        are filled with eastern ways;They are  soothsayers like the Philistines,And
        they are pleased with the children of foreigners.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Their land is also full of silver and gold,And there is no end to
        their treasures;Their land is also full of horses,And there is no end to
        their chariots.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Their land is also full of idols;They worship the work of their own
        hands,That which their own fingers have made.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: People bow down,And each man humbles himself;Therefore do not forgive
        them.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Enter into the rock, and hide in the dust,From the terror of the LordAnd
        the glory of His majesty.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: The lofty looks of man shall be humbled,The haughtiness of men shall
        be bowed down,And the Lord alone shall be exalted in that day.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "For the day of the Lord of hostsShall  come upon everything proud
        and lofty,Upon everything lifted up\u2014And it shall be brought low\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Upon all the cedars of Lebanon that  are high and lifted up,And upon
        all the oaks of Bashan;
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Upon all the high mountains,And upon all the hills that  are lifted
        up;
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Upon every high tower,And upon every fortified wall;
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Upon all the ships of Tarshish,And upon all the beautiful sloops.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: The loftiness of man shall be bowed down,And the haughtiness of men
        shall be brought low;The Lord alone will be exalted in that day,
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: But the idols He shall utterly abolish.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: They shall go into the holes of the rocks,And into the caves of the
        earth,From the terror of the LordAnd the glory of His majesty,When He arises
        to shake the earth mightily.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: In that day a man will cast away his idols of silverAnd his idols
        of gold,Which they made, each for himself to worship,To the moles and bats,
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: To go into the clefts of the rocks,And into the crags of the rugged
        rocks,From the terror of the LordAnd the glory of His majesty,When He arises
        to shake the earth mightily.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Sever yourselves from such a man,Whose breath is in his nostrils;For
        of what account is he?
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judgment on Judah and Jerusalem'
      title: Judgment on Judah and Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: For behold, the Lord, the Lord of hosts,Takes away from Jerusalem
        and from JudahThe stock and the store,The whole supply of bread and the whole
        supply of water;
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: The mighty man and the man of war,The judge and the prophet,And the
        diviner and the elder;
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: The captain of fifty and the honorable man,The counselor and the skillful
        artisan,And the expert enchanter.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CI will give children to  be their princes,And babes shall rule
        over them."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "The people will be oppressed,Every one by another and every one by
        his neighbor;The child will be insolent toward the elder,And the base toward
        the honorable.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "When a man takes hold of his brotherIn the house of his father, saying,\u201CYou
        have clothing;You be our ruler,And let these ruins be under your power,\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "In that day he will protest, saying,\u201CI cannot cure your ills,For
        in my house is neither food nor clothing;Do not make me a ruler of the people.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: For Jerusalem stumbled,And Judah is fallen,Because their tongue and
        their doingsAre against the Lord,To provoke the eyes of His glory.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: The look on their countenance witnesses against them,And they declare
        their sin as Sodom;They do not hide it.Woe to their soul!For they have brought
        evil upon themselves.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CSay to the righteous that it  shall  be well with  them,For
        they shall eat the fruit of their doings."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Woe to the wicked! It  shall  be ill with  him,For the reward of his
        hands shall be given him.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Oppression and Luxury Condemned'
      title: Oppression and Luxury Condemned
      number: 12
      content: "As  for My people, children are their oppressors,And women rule over
        them.O My people! Those who lead you cause you to err,And destroy the way
        of your paths.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: The Lord stands up to plead,And stands to judge the people.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "The Lord will enter into judgmentWith the elders of His peopleAnd
        His princes:\u201CFor you have eaten up the vineyard;The plunder of the poor
        is in your houses."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "What do you mean by crushing My peopleAnd grinding the faces of the
        poor?\u201DSays the Lord God of hosts."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Moreover the Lord says:\u201CBecause the daughters of Zion are haughty,And
        walk with outstretched necksAnd wanton eyes,Walking and mincing as they go,Making
        a jingling with their feet,"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Therefore the Lord will strike with a scabThe crown of the head of
        the daughters of Zion,And the Lord will uncover their secret parts.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: In that day the Lord will take away the finery:The jingling anklets,
        the scarves, and the crescents;
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: The pendants, the bracelets, and the veils;
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: The headdresses, the leg ornaments, and the headbands;The perfume
        boxes, the charms,
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: and the rings;The nose jewels,
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: the festal apparel, and the mantles;The outer garments, the purses,
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: and the mirrors;The fine linen, the turbans, and the robes.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: And so it shall be:Instead of a sweet smell there will be a stench;Instead
        of a sash, a rope;Instead of well-set hair, baldness;Instead of a rich robe,
        a girding of sackcloth;And branding instead of beauty.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Your men shall fall by the sword,And your mighty in the war.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: Her gates shall lament and mourn,And she being desolate shall sit
        on the ground.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Renewal of Zion'
      title: The Renewal of Zion
      number: 1
      content: "And in that day seven women shall take hold of one man, saying,\u201CWe
        will eat our own food and wear our own apparel;Only let us be called by your
        name,To take away our reproach.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: In that day the Branch of the Lord shall be beautiful and glorious;And
        the fruit of the earth shall  be excellent and appealingFor those of Israel
        who have escaped.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And it shall come to pass that he  who  is left in Zion and remains
        in Jerusalem will be called holy\u2014everyone who is recorded among the
        living in Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'When the Lord has washed away the filth of the daughters of Zion,
        and purged the blood of Jerusalem from her midst, by the spirit of judgment
        and by the spirit of burning, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'then the Lord will create above every dwelling place of Mount Zion,
        and above her assemblies, a cloud and smoke by day and the shining of a flaming
        fire by night. For over all the glory there will  be a covering. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: And there will be a tabernacle for shade in the daytime from the heat,
        for a place of refuge, and for a shelter from storm and rain.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Disappointing Vineyard"
      title: "God\u2019s Disappointing Vineyard"
      number: 1
      content: Now let me sing to my Well-belovedA song of my Beloved regarding His
        vineyard:My Well-beloved has a vineyardOn a very fruitful hill.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: He dug it up and cleared out its stones,And planted it with the choicest
        vine.He built a tower in its midst,And also made a winepress in it;So He
        expected it to bring forth good grapes,But it brought forth wild grapes.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CAnd now, O inhabitants of Jerusalem and men of Judah,Judge,
        please, between Me and My vineyard."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: What more could have been done to My vineyardThat I have not done
        in it?Why then, when I expected it to bring forth good grapes,Did it bring
        forth wild grapes?
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: And now, please let Me tell you what I will do to My vineyard:I will
        take away its hedge, and it shall be burned;And break down its wall, and
        it shall be trampled down.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "I will lay it waste;It shall not be pruned or dug,But there shall
        come up briers and thorns.I will also command the cloudsThat they rain no
        rain on it.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Impending Judgment on Excesses'
      title: Impending Judgment on Excesses
      number: 7
      content: For the vineyard of the Lord of hosts is the house of Israel,And the
        men of Judah are His pleasant plant.He looked for justice, but behold, oppression;For
        righteousness, but behold, a cry for  help.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Woe to those who join house to house;They add field to field,Till
        there  is no placeWhere they may dwell alone in the midst of the land!
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "In my hearing the Lord of hosts said,\u201CTruly, many houses shall
        be desolate,Great and beautiful ones, without inhabitant."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "For ten acres of vineyard shall yield one bath,And a homer of seed
        shall yield one ephah.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Woe to those who rise early in the morning,That they may follow intoxicating
        drink;Who continue until night, till wine inflames them!
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: The harp and the strings,The tambourine and flute,And wine are in
        their feasts;But they do not regard the work of the Lord,Nor consider the
        operation of His hands.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Therefore my people have gone into captivity,Because they  have no
        knowledge;Their honorable men are famished,And their multitude dried up with
        thirst.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Therefore Sheol has enlarged itselfAnd opened its mouth beyond measure;Their
        glory and their multitude and their pomp,And he who is jubilant, shall descend
        into it.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: People shall be brought down,Each man shall be humbled,And the eyes
        of the lofty shall be humbled.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: But the Lord of hosts shall be exalted in judgment,And God who is
        holy shall be hallowed in righteousness.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Then the lambs shall feed in their pasture,And in the waste places
        of the fat ones strangers shall eat.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Woe to those who draw iniquity with cords of vanity,And sin as if
        with a cart rope;
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "That say, \u201CLet Him make speed and hasten His work,That we may
        see it;And let the counsel of the Holy One of Israel draw near and come,That
        we may know it.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Woe to those who call evil good, and good evil;Who put darkness for
        light, and light for darkness;Who put bitter for sweet, and sweet for bitter!
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Woe to those  who  are  wise in their own eyes,And prudent in their
        own sight!
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Woe to men mighty at drinking wine,Woe to men valiant for mixing intoxicating
        drink,
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Who justify the wicked for a bribe,And take away justice from the
        righteous man!
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: Therefore, as the fire devours the stubble,And the flame consumes
        the chaff,So  their root will be as rottenness,And their blossom will ascend
        like dust;Because they have rejected the law of the Lord of hosts,And despised
        the word of the Holy One of Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Therefore the anger of the Lord is aroused against His people;He has
        stretched out His hand against themAnd stricken them,And the hills trembled.Their
        carcasses were as refuse in the midst of the streets.For all this His anger
        is not turned away,But His hand is stretched out still.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: He will lift up a banner to the nations from afar,And will whistle
        to them from the end of the earth;Surely they shall come with speed, swiftly.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: No one will be weary or stumble among them,No one will slumber or
        sleep;Nor will the belt on their loins be loosed,Nor the strap of their sandals
        be broken;
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Whose arrows are sharp,And all their bows bent;Their horses\u2019
        hooves will seem like flint,And their wheels like a whirlwind."
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: Their roaring will  be like a lion,They will roar like young lions;Yes,
        they will roarAnd lay hold of the prey;They will carry it away safely,And
        no one will deliver.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: In that day they will roar against themLike the roaring of the sea.And
        if one  looks to the land,Behold, darkness and sorrow;And the light is darkened
        by the clouds.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Isaiah Called to Be a Prophet'
      title: Isaiah Called to Be a Prophet
      number: 1
      content: 'In the year that King Uzziah died, I saw the Lord sitting on a throne,
        high and lifted up, and the train of His robe filled the temple. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Above it stood seraphim; each one had six wings: with two he covered
        his face, with two he covered his feet, and with two he flew. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And one cried to another and said:\u201CHoly, holy, holy is the Lord
        of hosts;The whole earth is full of His glory!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: And the posts of the door were shaken by the voice of him who cried
        out, and the house was filled with smoke.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So I said:\u201CWoe is me, for I am undone!Because I am a man of
        unclean lips,And I dwell in the midst of a people of unclean lips;For my
        eyes have seen the King,The Lord of hosts.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then one of the seraphim flew to me, having in his hand a live coal
        which he had taken with the tongs from the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And he touched my mouth with  it, and said:\u201CBehold, this has
        touched your lips;Your iniquity is taken away,And your sin purged.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Also I heard the voice of the Lord, saying:\u201CWhom shall I send,And
        who will go for Us?\u201DThen I said, \u201CHere am I! Send me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And He said, \u201CGo, and tell this people:\u2018Keep on hearing,
        but do not understand;Keep on seeing, but do not perceive.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CMake the heart of this people dull,And their ears heavy,And
        shut their eyes;Lest they see with their eyes,And hear with their ears,And
        understand with their heart,And return and be healed.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then I said, \u201CLord, how long?\u201DAnd He answered:\u201CUntil
        the cities are laid waste and without inhabitant,The houses are without a
        man,The land is utterly desolate,"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: The Lord has removed men far away,And the forsaken places are many
        in the midst of the land.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But yet a tenth will  be in it,And will return and be for consuming,As
        a terebinth tree or as an oak,Whose stump remains when it is cut down.So
        the holy seed shall  be its stump.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Isaiah Sent to King Ahaz'
      title: Isaiah Sent to King Ahaz
      number: 1
      content: 'Now it came to pass in the days of Ahaz the son of Jotham, the son
        of Uzziah, king of Judah, that Rezin king of Syria and Pekah the son of Remaliah,
        king of Israel, went up to Jerusalem to make war against it, but could not
        prevail against it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And it was told to the house of David, saying, \u201CSyria\u2019s
        forces are deployed in Ephraim.\u201D So his heart and the heart of his people
        were moved as the trees of the woods are moved with the wind."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then the Lord said to Isaiah, \u201CGo out now to meet Ahaz, you
        and Shear-Jashub your son, at the end of the aqueduct from the upper pool,
        on the highway to the Fuller\u2019s Field, "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "and say to him: \u2018Take heed, and be quiet; do not fear or be
        fainthearted for these two stubs of smoking firebrands, for the fierce anger
        of Rezin and Syria, and the son of Remaliah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Because Syria, Ephraim, and the son of Remaliah have plotted evil
        against you, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CLet us go up against Judah and trouble it, and let us make
        a gap in its wall for ourselves, and set a king over them, the son of Tabel\u201D\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "thus says the Lord God:\u201CIt shall not stand,Nor shall it come
        to pass."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: For the head of Syria is Damascus,And the head of Damascus is Rezin.Within
        sixty-five years Ephraim will be broken,So  that  it  will not be a people.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: The Immanuel Prophecy'
      title: The Immanuel Prophecy
      number: 9
      content: "The head of Ephraim is Samaria,And the head of Samaria is Remaliah\u2019s
        son.If you will not believe,Surely you shall not be established.\u201D \u2019
        \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Moreover the Lord spoke again to Ahaz, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CAsk a sign for yourself from the Lord your God; ask it either
        in the depth or in the height above.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But Ahaz said, \u201CI will not ask, nor will I test the Lord!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then he said, \u201CHear now, O house of David! Is  it a small thing
        for you to weary men, but will you weary my God also? "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Therefore the Lord Himself will give you a sign: Behold, the virgin
        shall conceive and bear a Son, and shall call His name Immanuel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Curds and honey He shall eat, that He may know to refuse the evil
        and choose the good. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For before the Child shall know to refuse the evil and choose the
        good, the land that you dread will be forsaken by both her kings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "The Lord will bring the king of Assyria upon you and your people
        and your father\u2019s house\u2014days that have not come since the day that
        Ephraim departed from Judah.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: And it shall come to pass in that dayThat the Lord  will whistle for
        the flyThat is in the farthest part of the rivers of Egypt,And for the bee
        that is in the land of Assyria.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: They will come, and all of them will restIn the desolate valleys and
        in the clefts of the rocks,And on all thorns and in all pastures.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: In the same day the Lord will shave with a hired razor,With those
        from beyond the River, with the king of Assyria,The head and the hair of
        the legs,And will also remove the beard.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: It shall be in that dayThat a man will keep alive a young cow and
        two sheep;
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: So it shall be, from the abundance of milk they give,That he will
        eat curds;For curds and honey everyone will eat who is left in the land.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: It shall happen in that day,That wherever there could be a thousand
        vinesWorth a thousand shekels of silver,It will be for briers and thorns.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: With arrows and bows men will come there,Because all the land will
        become briers and thorns.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: And to any hill which could be dug with the hoe,You will not go there
        for fear of briers and thorns;But it will become a range for oxenAnd a place
        for sheep to roam.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Assyria Will Invade the Land'
      title: Assyria Will Invade the Land
      number: 1
      content: "Moreover the Lord said to me, \u201CTake a large scroll, and write
        on it with a man\u2019s pen concerning Maher-Shalal-Hash-Baz. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And I will take for Myself faithful witnesses to record, Uriah the
        priest and Zechariah the son of Jeberechiah.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then I went to the prophetess, and she conceived and bore a son.
        Then the Lord said to me, \u201CCall his name Maher-Shalal-Hash-Baz; "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "for before the child shall have knowledge to cry \u2018My father\u2019
        and \u2018My mother,\u2019 the riches of Damascus and the spoil of Samaria
        will be taken away before the king of Assyria.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The Lord also spoke to me again, saying:'
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CInasmuch as these people refusedThe waters of Shiloah that
        flow softly,And rejoice in Rezin and in Remaliah\u2019s son;"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Now therefore, behold, the Lord brings up over themThe waters of
        the River, strong and mighty\u2014The king of Assyria and all his glory;He
        will go up over all his channelsAnd go over all his banks."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: He will pass through Judah,He will overflow and pass over,He will
        reach up to the neck;And the stretching out of his wingsWill fill the breadth
        of Your land, O Immanuel.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CBe shattered, O you peoples, and be broken in pieces!Give ear,
        all you from far countries.Gird yourselves, but be broken in pieces;Gird
        yourselves, but be broken in pieces."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Fear God, Heed His Word'
      title: Fear God, Heed His Word
      number: 10
      content: "Take counsel together, but it will come to nothing;Speak the word,
        but it will not stand,For God is with us.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For the Lord spoke thus to me with a strong hand, and instructed
        me that I should not walk in the way of this people, saying:'
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CDo not say, \u2018A conspiracy,\u2019Concerning all that this
        people call a conspiracy,Nor be afraid of their threats, nor be troubled."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: The Lord of hosts, Him you shall hallow;Let Him be your fear,And let
        Him be your dread.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: He will be as a sanctuary,But a stone of stumbling and a rock of offenseTo
        both the houses of Israel,As a trap and a snare to the inhabitants of Jerusalem.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And many among them shall stumble;They shall fall and be broken,Be
        snared and taken.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Bind up the testimony,Seal the law among my disciples.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: And I will wait on the Lord,Who hides His face from the house of Jacob;And
        I will hope in Him.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Here am I and the children whom the Lord has given me!We  are for
        signs and wonders in IsraelFrom the Lord of hosts,Who dwells in Mount Zion.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And when they say to you, \u201CSeek those who are mediums and wizards,
        who whisper and mutter,\u201D should not a people seek their God? Should 
        they  seek the dead on behalf of the living? "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: To the law and to the testimony! If they do not speak according to
        this word, it  is because there is no light in them.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'They will pass through it hard-pressed and hungry; and it shall happen,
        when they are hungry, that they will be enraged and curse their king and
        their God, and look upward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Then they will look to the earth, and see trouble and darkness, gloom
        of anguish; and they  will  be driven into darkness.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Government of the Promised Son'
      title: The Government of the Promised Son
      number: 1
      content: Nevertheless the gloom will not be upon her who is distressed,As when
        at first He lightly esteemedThe land of Zebulun and the land of Naphtali,And
        afterward more heavily oppressed her,By the way of the sea, beyond the Jordan,In
        Galilee of the Gentiles.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: The people who walked in darknessHave seen a great light;Those who
        dwelt in the land of the shadow of death,Upon them a light has shined.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: You have multiplied the nationAnd increased its joy;They rejoice before
        YouAccording to the joy of harvest,As men rejoice when they divide the spoil.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: For You have broken the yoke of his burdenAnd the staff of his shoulder,The
        rod of his oppressor,As in the day of Midian.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For every warrior\u2019s sandal from the noisy battle,And garments
        rolled in blood,Will be used for burning and fuel of fire."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: For unto us a Child is born,Unto us a Son is given;And the government
        will be upon His shoulder.And His name will be calledWonderful, Counselor,
        Mighty God,Everlasting Father, Prince of Peace.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: The Punishment of Samaria'
      title: The Punishment of Samaria
      number: 7
      content: Of the increase of His government and peaceThere  will  be no end,Upon
        the throne of David and over His kingdom,To order it and establish it with
        judgment and justiceFrom that time forward, even forever.The zeal of the
        Lord of hosts will perform this.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: The Lord sent a word against Jacob,And it has fallen on Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "All the people will know\u2014Ephraim and the inhabitant of Samaria\u2014Who
        say in pride and arrogance of heart:"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CThe bricks have fallen down,But we will rebuild with hewn stones;The
        sycamores are cut down,But we will replace them with cedars.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Therefore the Lord shall set upThe adversaries of Rezin against him,And
        spur his enemies on,
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: The Syrians before and the Philistines behind;And they shall devour
        Israel with an open mouth.For all this His anger is not turned away,But His
        hand is stretched out still.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: For the people do not turn to Him who strikes them,Nor do they seek
        the Lord of hosts.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Therefore the Lord will cut off head and tail from Israel,Palm branch
        and bulrush in one day.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: The elder and honorable, he is the head;The prophet who teaches lies,
        he is the tail.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: For the leaders of this people cause them to err,And those  who  are
        led by them are destroyed.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Therefore the Lord will have no joy in their young men,Nor have mercy
        on their fatherless and widows;For everyone is a hypocrite and an evildoer,And
        every mouth speaks folly.For all this His anger is not turned away,But His
        hand is stretched out still.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: For wickedness burns as the fire;It shall devour the briers and thorns,And
        kindle in the thickets of the forest;They shall mount up like rising smoke.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Through the wrath of the Lord of hostsThe land is burned up,And the
        people shall be as fuel for the fire;No man shall spare his brother.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: And he shall snatch on the right handAnd be hungry;He shall devour
        on the left handAnd not be satisfied;Every man shall eat the flesh of his
        own arm.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Manasseh shall  devour Ephraim, and Ephraim Manasseh;Together they
        shall  be  against Judah.For all this His anger is not turned away,But His
        hand is stretched out still.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CWoe to those who decree unrighteous decrees,Who write misfortune,Which
        they have prescribed"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: To rob the needy of justice,And to take what is right from the poor
        of My people,That widows may be their prey,And that they may rob the fatherless.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: What will you do in the day of punishment,And in the desolation which
        will come from afar?To whom will you flee for help?And where will you leave
        your glory?
      comments: []
    - name: '4: Arrogant Assyria Also Judged'
      title: Arrogant Assyria Also Judged
      number: 4
      content: "Without Me they shall bow down among the prisoners,And they shall
        fall among the slain.\u201DFor all this His anger is not turned away,But
        His hand is stretched out still."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CWoe to Assyria, the rod of My angerAnd the staff in whose hand
        is My indignation."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: I will send him against an ungodly nation,And against the people of
        My wrathI will give him charge,To seize the spoil, to take the prey,And to
        tread them down like the mire of the streets.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Yet he does not mean so,Nor does his heart think so;But it  is in
        his heart to destroy,And cut off not a few nations.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "For he says,\u2018Are not my princes altogether kings?"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Is not Calno like Carchemish?Is not Hamath like Arpad?Is not Samaria
        like Damascus?
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: As my hand has found the kingdoms of the idols,Whose carved images
        excelled those of Jerusalem and Samaria,
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "As I have done to Samaria and her idols,Shall I not do also to Jerusalem
        and her idols?\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Therefore it shall come to pass, when the Lord has performed all
        His work on Mount Zion and on Jerusalem, that  He  will  say,  \u201CI will
        punish the fruit of the arrogant heart of the king of Assyria, and the glory
        of his haughty looks.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "For he says:\u201CBy the strength of my hand I have done it,And by
        my wisdom, for I am prudent;Also I have removed the boundaries of the people,And
        have robbed their treasuries;So I have put down the inhabitants like a valiant
        man."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "My hand has found like a nest the riches of the people,And as one
        gathers eggs that  are left,I have gathered all the earth;And there was no
        one who moved his wing,Nor opened his mouth with even a peep.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Shall the ax boast itself against him who chops with it?Or shall the
        saw exalt itself against him who saws with it?As if a rod could wield itself
        against those who lift it up,Or as if a staff could lift up, as  if  it 
        were not wood!
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Therefore the Lord, the Lord of hosts,Will send leanness among his
        fat ones;And under his gloryHe will kindle a burningLike the burning of a
        fire.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: So the Light of Israel will be for a fire,And his Holy One for a flame;It
        will burn and devourHis thorns and his briers in one day.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: And it will consume the glory of his forest and of his fruitful field,Both
        soul and body;And they will be as when a sick man wastes away.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: The Returning Remnant of Israel'
      title: The Returning Remnant of Israel
      number: 19
      content: Then the rest of the trees of his forestWill be so few in numberThat
        a child may write them.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: And it shall come to pass in that dayThat the remnant of Israel,And
        such as have escaped of the house of Jacob,Will never again depend on him
        who defeated them,But will depend on the Lord, the Holy One of Israel, in
        truth.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: The remnant will return, the remnant of Jacob,To the Mighty God.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: For though your people, O Israel, be as the sand of the sea,A remnant
        of them will return;The destruction decreed shall overflow with righteousness.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: For the Lord God of hostsWill make a determined endIn the midst of
        all the land.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord God of hosts: \u201CO My people, who
        dwell in Zion, do not be afraid of the Assyrian. He shall strike you with
        a rod and lift up his staff against you, in the manner of Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "For yet a very little while and the indignation will cease, as will
        My anger in their destruction.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: And the Lord of hosts will stir up a scourge for him like the slaughter
        of Midian at the rock of Oreb; as His rod was on the sea, so will He lift
        it up in the manner of Egypt.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: It shall come to pass in that dayThat his burden will be taken away
        from your shoulder,And his yoke from your neck,And the yoke will be destroyed
        because of the anointing oil.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: He has come to Aiath,He has passed Migron;At Michmash he has attended
        to his equipment.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: They have gone along the ridge,They have taken up lodging at Geba.Ramah
        is afraid,Gibeah of Saul has fled.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Lift up your voice,O daughter of Gallim!Cause it to be heard as far
        as Laish\u2014O poor Anathoth!"
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: Madmenah has fled,The inhabitants of Gebim seek refuge.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: As yet he will remain at Nob that day;He will shake his fist at the
        mount of the daughter of Zion,The hill of Jerusalem.
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: Behold, the Lord,The Lord of hosts,Will lop off the bough with terror;Those
        of high stature will  be hewn down,And the haughty will be humbled.
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: He will cut down the thickets of the forest with iron,And Lebanon
        will fall by the Mighty One.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The Reign of Jesse\u2019s Offspring"
      title: "The Reign of Jesse\u2019s Offspring"
      number: 1
      content: There shall come forth a Rod from the stem of Jesse,And a Branch shall
        grow out of his roots.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: The Spirit of the Lord shall rest upon Him,The Spirit of wisdom and
        understanding,The Spirit of counsel and might,The Spirit of knowledge and
        of the fear of the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: His delight is in the fear of the Lord,And He shall not judge by the
        sight of His eyes,Nor decide by the hearing of His ears;
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: But with righteousness He shall judge the poor,And decide with equity
        for the meek of the earth;He shall strike the earth with the rod of His mouth,And
        with the breath of His lips He shall slay the wicked.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Righteousness shall be the belt of His loins,And faithfulness the
        belt of His waist.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CThe wolf also shall dwell with the lamb,The leopard shall lie
        down with the young goat,The calf and the young lion and the fatling together;And
        a little child shall lead them."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: The cow and the bear shall graze;Their young ones shall lie down together;And
        the lion shall eat straw like the ox.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The nursing child shall play by the cobra\u2019s hole,And the weaned
        child shall put his hand in the viper\u2019s den."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: They shall not hurt nor destroy in all My holy mountain,For the earth
        shall be full of the knowledge of the LordAs the waters cover the sea.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CAnd in that day there shall be a Root of Jesse,Who shall stand
        as a banner to the people;For the Gentiles shall seek Him,And His resting
        place shall be glorious.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: It shall come to pass in that dayThat the Lord shall set His hand
        again the second timeTo recover the remnant of His people who are left,From
        Assyria and Egypt,From Pathros and Cush,From Elam and Shinar,From Hamath
        and the islands of the sea.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: He will set up a banner for the nations,And will assemble the outcasts
        of Israel,And gather together the dispersed of JudahFrom the four corners
        of the earth.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Also the envy of Ephraim shall depart,And the adversaries of Judah
        shall be cut off;Ephraim shall not envy Judah,And Judah shall not harass
        Ephraim.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: But they shall fly down upon the shoulder of the Philistines toward
        the west;Together they shall plunder the people of the East;They shall lay
        their hand on Edom and Moab;And the people of Ammon shall obey them.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: The Lord  will utterly destroy the tongue of the Sea of Egypt;With
        His mighty wind He will shake His fist over the River,And strike it in the
        seven streams,And make men cross over dry-shod.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: There will be a highway for the remnant of His peopleWho will be left
        from Assyria,As it was for IsraelIn the day that he came up from the land
        of Egypt.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Hymn of Praise'
      title: A Hymn of Praise
      number: 1
      content: "And in that day you will say:\u201CO Lord, I will praise You;Though
        You were angry with me,Your anger is turned away, and You comfort me."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Behold, God is my salvation,I will trust and not be afraid;\u2018For
        Yah, the Lord, is my strength and song;He also has become my salvation.\u2019
        \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Therefore with joy you will draw waterFrom the wells of salvation.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And in that day you will say:\u201CPraise the Lord, call upon His
        name;Declare His deeds among the peoples,Make mention that His name is exalted."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Sing to the Lord,For He has done excellent things;This is known in
        all the earth.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Cry out and shout, O inhabitant of Zion,For great is  the Holy One
        of Israel in your midst!\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Proclamation Against Babylon'
      title: Proclamation Against Babylon
      number: 1
      content: The burden against Babylon which Isaiah the son of Amoz saw.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CLift up a banner on the high mountain,Raise your voice to them;Wave
        your hand, that they may enter the gates of the nobles."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "I have commanded My sanctified ones;I have also called My mighty
        ones for My anger\u2014Those who rejoice in My exaltation.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: The noise of a multitude in the mountains,Like that of many people!A
        tumultuous noise of the kingdoms of nations gathered together!The Lord of
        hosts mustersThe army for battle.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "They come from a far country,From the end of heaven\u2014The Lord
        and His weapons of indignation,To destroy the whole land."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Wail, for the day of the Lord  is at hand!It will come as destruction
        from the Almighty.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Therefore all hands will be limp,Every man\u2019s heart will melt,"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: And they will be afraid.Pangs and sorrows will take hold of them;They
        will be in pain as a woman in childbirth;They will be amazed at one another;Their
        faces will  be  like flames.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Behold, the day of the Lord comes,Cruel, with both wrath and fierce
        anger,To lay the land desolate;And He will destroy its sinners from it.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: For the stars of heaven and their constellationsWill not give their
        light;The sun will be darkened in its going forth,And the moon will not cause
        its light to shine.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CI will punish the world for its evil,And the wicked for their
        iniquity;I will halt the arrogance of the proud,And will lay low the haughtiness
        of the terrible."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: I will make a mortal more rare than fine gold,A man more than the
        golden wedge of Ophir.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Therefore I will shake the heavens,And the earth will move out of
        her place,In the wrath of the Lord of hostsAnd in the day of His fierce anger.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: It shall be as the hunted gazelle,And as a sheep that no man takes
        up;Every man will turn to his own people,And everyone will flee to his own
        land.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Everyone who is found will be thrust through,And everyone who is captured
        will fall by the sword.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Their children also will be dashed to pieces before their eyes;Their
        houses will be plunderedAnd their wives ravished.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CBehold, I will stir up the Medes against them,Who will not
        regard silver;And as  for gold, they will not delight in it."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Also their bows will dash the young men to pieces,And they will have
        no pity on the fruit of the womb;Their eye will not spare children.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And Babylon, the glory of kingdoms,The beauty of the Chaldeans\u2019
        pride,Will be as when God overthrew Sodom and Gomorrah."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: It will never be inhabited,Nor will it be settled from generation
        to generation;Nor will the Arabian pitch tents there,Nor will the shepherds
        make their sheepfolds there.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: But wild beasts of the desert will lie there,And their houses will
        be full of owls;Ostriches will dwell there,And wild goats will caper there.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "The hyenas will howl in their citadels,And jackals in their pleasant
        palaces.Her time is near to come,And her days will not be prolonged.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Mercy on Jacob'
      title: Mercy on Jacob
      number: 1
      content: 'For the Lord  will have mercy on Jacob, and will still choose Israel,
        and settle them in their own land. The strangers will be joined with them,
        and they will cling to the house of Jacob. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: Fall of the King of Babylon'
      title: Fall of the King of Babylon
      number: 2
      content: Then people will take them and bring them to their place, and the
        house of Israel will possess them for servants and maids in the land of the
        Lord; they will take them captive whose captives they were, and rule over
        their oppressors.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'It shall come to pass in the day the Lord gives you rest from your
        sorrow, and from your fear and the hard bondage in which you were made to
        serve, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "that you will take up this proverb against the king of Babylon, and
        say:\u201CHow the oppressor has ceased,The golden city ceased!"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: The Lord has broken the staff of the wicked,The scepter of the rulers;
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: He who struck the people in wrath with a continual stroke,He who ruled
        the nations in anger,Is persecuted and no one hinders.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: The whole earth is at rest and quiet;They break forth into singing.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Indeed the cypress trees rejoice over you,And the cedars of Lebanon,Saying,
        \u2018Since you were cut down,No woodsman has come up against us.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CHell from beneath is excited about you,To meet you at your
        coming;It stirs up the dead for you,All the chief ones of the earth;It has
        raised up from their thronesAll the kings of the nations."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "They all shall speak and say to you:\u2018Have you also become as
        weak as we?Have you become like us?"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: The Fall of Lucifer'
      title: The Fall of Lucifer
      number: 11
      content: "Your pomp is brought down to Sheol,And the sound of your stringed
        instruments;The maggot is spread under you,And worms cover you.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CHow you are fallen from heaven,O Lucifer, son of the morning!How
        you are cut down to the ground,You who weakened the nations!"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "For you have said in your heart:\u2018I will ascend into heaven,I
        will exalt my throne above the stars of God;I will also sit on the mount
        of the congregationOn the farthest sides of the north;"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "I will ascend above the heights of the clouds,I will be like the
        Most High.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Yet you shall be brought down to Sheol,To the lowest depths of the
        Pit.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CThose who see you will gaze at you,And consider you, saying:\u2018Is
        this the man who made the earth tremble,Who shook kingdoms,"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Who made the world as a wildernessAnd destroyed its cities,Who did
        not open the house of his prisoners?\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CAll the kings of the nations,All of them, sleep in glory,Everyone
        in his own house;"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: But you are cast out of your graveLike an abominable branch,Like the
        garment of those who are slain,Thrust through with a sword,Who go down to
        the stones of the pit,Like a corpse trodden underfoot.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: You will not be joined with them in burial,Because you have destroyed
        your landAnd slain your people.The brood of evildoers shall never be named.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Babylon Destroyed'
      title: Babylon Destroyed
      number: 21
      content: "Prepare slaughter for his childrenBecause of the iniquity of their
        fathers,Lest they rise up and possess the land,And fill the face of the world
        with cities.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CFor I will rise up against them,\u201D says the Lord of hosts,\u201CAnd
        cut off from Babylon the name and remnant,And offspring and posterity,\u201D
        says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Assyria Destroyed'
      title: Assyria Destroyed
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CI will also make it a possession for the porcupine,And marshes
        of muddy water;I will sweep it with the broom of destruction,\u201D says
        the Lord of hosts."
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "The Lord of hosts has sworn, saying,\u201CSurely, as I have thought,
        so it shall come to pass,And as I have purposed, so it shall stand:"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: That I will break the Assyrian in My land,And on My mountains tread
        him underfoot.Then his yoke shall be removed from them,And his burden removed
        from their shoulders.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: This is the purpose that is purposed against the whole earth,And this
        is the hand that is stretched out over all the nations.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: Philistia Destroyed'
      title: Philistia Destroyed
      number: 27
      content: "For the Lord of hosts has purposed,And who will annul it?His hand
        is stretched out,And who will turn it back?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: This is the burden which came in the year that King Ahaz died.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CDo not rejoice, all you of Philistia,Because the rod that struck
        you is broken;For out of the serpent\u2019s roots will come forth a viper,And
        its offspring will  be a fiery flying serpent."
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: The firstborn of the poor will feed,And the needy will lie down in
        safety;I will kill your roots with famine,And it will slay your remnant.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Wail, O gate! Cry, O city!All you of Philistia are dissolved;For
        smoke will come from the north,And no one will  be alone in his appointed
        times.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: What will they answer the messengers of the nation?That the Lord has
        founded Zion,And the poor of His people shall take refuge in it.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Proclamation Against Moab'
      title: Proclamation Against Moab
      number: 1
      content: The burden against Moab.Because in the night Ar of Moab is laid wasteAnd
        destroyed,Because in the night Kir of Moab is laid wasteAnd destroyed,
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: He has gone up to the temple and Dibon,To the high places to weep.Moab
        will wail over Nebo and over Medeba;On all their heads will  be baldness,And
        every beard cut off.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: In their streets they will clothe themselves with sackcloth;On the
        tops of their housesAnd in their streetsEveryone will wail, weeping bitterly.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Heshbon and Elealeh will cry out,Their voice shall be heard as far
        as Jahaz;Therefore the armed soldiers of Moab will cry out;His life will
        be burdensome to him.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CMy heart will cry out for Moab;His fugitives shall  flee to
        Zoar,Like a three-year-old heifer.For by the Ascent of LuhithThey will go
        up with weeping;For in the way of HoronaimThey will raise up a cry of destruction,"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: For the waters of Nimrim will be desolate,For the green grass has
        withered away;The grass fails, there is nothing green.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Therefore the abundance they have gained,And what they have laid up,They
        will carry away to the Brook of the Willows.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: For the cry has gone all around the borders of Moab,Its wailing to
        EglaimAnd its wailing to Beer Elim.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "For the waters of Dimon will be full of blood;Because I will bring
        more upon Dimon,Lions upon him who escapes from Moab,And on the remnant of
        the land.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Moab Destroyed'
      title: Moab Destroyed
      number: 1
      content: Send the lamb to the ruler of the land,From Sela to the wilderness,To
        the mount of the daughter of Zion.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: For it shall be as a wandering bird thrown out of the nest;So shall
        be the daughters of Moab at the fords of the Arnon.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CTake counsel, execute judgment;Make your shadow like the night
        in the middle of the day;Hide the outcasts,Do not betray him who escapes."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Let My outcasts dwell with you, O Moab;Be a shelter to them from the
        face of the spoiler.For the extortioner is at an end,Devastation ceases,The
        oppressors are consumed out of the land.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "In mercy the throne will be established;And One will sit on it in
        truth, in the tabernacle of David,Judging and seeking justice and hastening
        righteousness.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "We have heard of the pride of Moab\u2014He  is very proud\u2014Of
        his haughtiness and his pride and his wrath;But his lies shall not be so."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Therefore Moab shall wail for Moab;Everyone shall wail.For the foundations
        of Kir Hareseth you shall mourn;Surely they  are stricken.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: For the fields of Heshbon languish,And  the vine of Sibmah;The lords
        of the nations have broken down its choice plants,Which have reached to JazerAnd
        wandered through the wilderness.Her branches are stretched out,They are gone
        over the sea.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Therefore I will bewail the vine of Sibmah,With the weeping of Jazer;I
        will drench you with my tears,O Heshbon and Elealeh;For battle cries have
        fallenOver your summer fruits and your harvest.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Gladness is taken away,And joy from the plentiful field;In the vineyards
        there will be no singing,Nor will there be shouting;No treaders will tread
        out wine in the presses;I have made their shouting cease.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Therefore my heart shall resound like a harp for Moab,And my inner
        being for Kir Heres.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: And it shall come to pass,When it is seen that Moab is weary on the
        high place,That he will come to his sanctuary to pray;But he will not prevail.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'This is the word which the Lord has spoken concerning Moab since
        that time. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But now the Lord has spoken, saying, \u201CWithin three years, as
        the years of a hired man, the glory of Moab will be despised with all that
        great multitude, and the remnant will  be very small and feeble.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Proclamation Against Syria and Israel'
      title: Proclamation Against Syria and Israel
      number: 1
      content: "The burden against Damascus.\u201CBehold, Damascus will cease from
        being a city,And it will be a ruinous heap."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: The cities of Aroer are forsaken;They will be for flocksWhich lie
        down, and no one will make them afraid.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "The fortress also will cease from Ephraim,The kingdom from Damascus,And
        the remnant of Syria;They will be as the glory of the children of Israel,\u201DSays
        the Lord of hosts."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CIn that day it shall come to passThat the glory of Jacob will
        wane,And the fatness of his flesh grow lean."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: It shall be as when the harvester gathers the grain,And reaps the
        heads with his arm;It shall be as he who gathers heads of grainIn the Valley
        of Rephaim.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Yet gleaning grapes will be left in it,Like the shaking of an olive
        tree,Two or three olives at the top of the uppermost bough,Four or five in
        its most fruitful branches,\u201DSays the Lord God of Israel."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: In that day a man will look to his Maker,And his eyes will have respect
        for the Holy One of Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: He will not look to the altars,The work of his hands;He will not respect
        what his fingers have made,Nor the wooden images nor the incense altars.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: In that day his strong cities will be as a forsaken boughAnd an uppermost
        branch,Which they left because of the children of Israel;And there will be
        desolation.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Because you have forgotten the God of your salvation,And have not
        been mindful of the Rock of your stronghold,Therefore you will plant pleasant
        plantsAnd set out foreign seedlings;
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: In the day you will make your plant to grow,And in the morning you
        will make your seed to flourish;But the harvest will  be a heap of ruinsIn
        the day of grief and desperate sorrow.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Woe to the multitude of many peopleWho make a noise like the roar
        of the seas,And to the rushing of nationsThat make a rushing like the rushing
        of mighty waters!
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: The nations will rush like the rushing of many waters;But God will
        rebuke them and they will flee far away,And be chased like the chaff of the
        mountains before the wind,Like a rolling thing before the whirlwind.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Then behold, at eventide, trouble!And before the morning, he is no
        more.This is the portion of those who plunder us,And the lot of those who
        rob us.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Proclamation Against Ethiopia'
      title: Proclamation Against Ethiopia
      number: 1
      content: Woe to the land shadowed with buzzing wings,Which is beyond the rivers
        of Ethiopia,
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Which sends ambassadors by sea,Even in vessels of reed on the waters,
        saying,\u201CGo, swift messengers, to a nation tall and smooth of  skin,To
        a people terrible from their beginning onward,A nation powerful and treading
        down,Whose land the rivers divide.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: All inhabitants of the world and dwellers on the earth:When he lifts
        up a banner on the mountains, you see it;And when he blows a trumpet, you
        hear it.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For so the Lord said to me,\u201CI will take My rest,And I will look
        from My dwelling placeLike clear heat in sunshine,Like a cloud of dew in
        the heat of harvest.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: For before the harvest, when the bud is perfectAnd the sour grape
        is ripening in the flower,He will both cut off the sprigs with pruning hooksAnd
        take away and cut down the branches.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: They will be left together for the mountain birds of preyAnd for the
        beasts of the earth;The birds of prey will summer on them,And all the beasts
        of the earth will winter on them.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "In that time a present will be brought to the Lord of hostsFrom a
        people tall and smooth of  skin,And from a people terrible from their beginning
        onward,A nation powerful and treading down,Whose land the rivers divide\u2014To
        the place of the name of the Lord of hosts,To Mount Zion."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Proclamation Against Egypt'
      title: Proclamation Against Egypt
      number: 1
      content: The burden against Egypt.Behold, the Lord  rides on a swift cloud,And
        will come into Egypt;The idols of Egypt will totter at His presence,And the
        heart of Egypt will melt in its midst.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CI will set Egyptians against Egyptians;Everyone will fight
        against his brother,And everyone against his neighbor,City against city,
        kingdom against kingdom."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: The spirit of Egypt will fail in its midst;I will destroy their counsel,And
        they will consult the idols and the charmers,The mediums and the sorcerers.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And the Egyptians I will giveInto the hand of a cruel master,And
        a fierce king will rule over them,\u201DSays the Lord, the Lord of hosts."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: The waters will fail from the sea,And the river will be wasted and
        dried up.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: The rivers will turn foul;The brooks of defense will be emptied and
        dried up;The reeds and rushes will wither.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: The papyrus reeds by the River, by the mouth of the River,And everything
        sown by the River,Will wither, be driven away, and be no more.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: The fishermen also will mourn;All those will lament who cast hooks
        into the River,And they will languish who spread nets on the waters.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Moreover those who work in fine flaxAnd those who weave fine fabric
        will be ashamed;
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: And its foundations will be broken.All who make wages will  be troubled
        of soul.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Surely the princes of Zoan are fools;Pharaoh\u2019s wise counselors
        give foolish counsel.How do you say to Pharaoh, \u201CI am the son of the
        wise,The son of ancient kings?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Where are they?Where are your wise men?Let them tell you now,And let
        them know what the Lord of hosts has purposed against Egypt.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: The princes of Zoan have become fools;The princes of Noph are deceived;They
        have also deluded Egypt,Those  who  are the mainstay of its tribes.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: The Lord has mingled a perverse spirit in her midst;And they have
        caused Egypt to err in all her work,As a drunken man staggers in his vomit.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Neither will there be any work for Egypt,Which the head or tail,Palm
        branch or bulrush, may do.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'In that day Egypt will be like women, and will be afraid and fear
        because of the waving of the hand of the Lord of hosts, which He waves over
        it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Egypt, Assyria, and Israel Blessed'
      title: Egypt, Assyria, and Israel Blessed
      number: 17
      content: And the land of Judah will be a terror to Egypt; everyone who makes
        mention of it will be afraid in himself, because of the counsel of the Lord
        of hosts which He has determined against it.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: In that day five cities in the land of Egypt will speak the language
        of Canaan and swear by the Lord of hosts; one will be called the City of
        Destruction.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'In that day there will be an altar to the Lord in the midst of the
        land of Egypt, and a pillar to the Lord at its border. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And it will be for a sign and for a witness to the Lord of hosts
        in the land of Egypt; for they will cry to the Lord because of the oppressors,
        and He will send them a Savior and a Mighty One, and He will deliver them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then the Lord will be known to Egypt, and the Egyptians will know
        the Lord in that day, and will make sacrifice and offering; yes, they will
        make a vow to the Lord and perform it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: And the Lord will strike Egypt, He will strike and heal it; they will
        return to the Lord, and He will be entreated by them and heal them.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: In that day there will be a highway from Egypt to Assyria, and the
        Assyrian will come into Egypt and the Egyptian into Assyria, and the Egyptians
        will serve with the Assyrians.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "In that day Israel will be one of three with Egypt and Assyria\u2014a
        blessing in the midst of the land, "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "whom the Lord of hosts shall bless, saying, \u201CBlessed is Egypt
        My people, and Assyria the work of My hands, and Israel My inheritance.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Sign Against Egypt and Ethiopia'
      title: The Sign Against Egypt and Ethiopia
      number: 1
      content: 'In the year that Tartan came to Ashdod, when Sargon the king of Assyria
        sent him, and he fought against Ashdod and took it, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "at the same time the Lord spoke by Isaiah the son of Amoz, saying,
        \u201CGo, and remove the sackcloth from your body, and take your sandals
        off your feet.\u201D And he did so, walking naked and barefoot."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then the Lord said, \u201CJust as My servant Isaiah has walked naked
        and barefoot three years for a sign and a wonder against Egypt and Ethiopia, "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'so shall the king of Assyria lead away the Egyptians as prisoners
        and the Ethiopians as captives, young and old, naked and barefoot, with their
        buttocks uncovered, to the shame of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then they shall be afraid and ashamed of Ethiopia their expectation
        and Egypt their glory. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the inhabitant of this territory will say in that day, \u2018Surely
        such is our expectation, wherever we flee for help to be delivered from the
        king of Assyria; and how shall we escape?\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Fall of Babylon Proclaimed'
      title: The Fall of Babylon Proclaimed
      number: 1
      content: The burden against the Wilderness of the Sea.As whirlwinds in the
        South pass through,So it comes from the desert, from a terrible land.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: A distressing vision is declared to me;The treacherous dealer deals
        treacherously,And the plunderer plunders.Go up, O Elam!Besiege, O Media!All
        its sighing I have made to cease.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Therefore my loins are filled with pain;Pangs have taken hold of me,
        like the pangs of a woman in labor.I was distressed when I heard it;I was
        dismayed when I saw it.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: My heart wavered, fearfulness frightened me;The night for which I
        longed He turned into fear for me.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Prepare the table,Set a watchman in the tower,Eat and drink.Arise,
        you princes,Anoint the shield!
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For thus has the Lord said to me:\u201CGo, set a watchman,Let him
        declare what he sees.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: And he saw a chariot with a pair of horsemen,A chariot of donkeys,
        and a chariot of camels,And he listened earnestly with great care.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then he cried, \u201CA lion, my Lord!I stand continually on the watchtower
        in the daytime;I have sat at my post every night."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And look, here comes a chariot of men with a pair of horsemen!\u201DThen
        he answered and said,\u201CBabylon is fallen, is fallen!And all the carved
        images of her godsHe has broken to the ground.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Proclamation Against Edom'
      title: Proclamation Against Edom
      number: 10
      content: Oh, my threshing and the grain of my floor!That which I have heard
        from the Lord of hosts,The God of Israel,I have declared to you.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "The burden against Dumah.He calls to me out of Seir,\u201CWatchman,
        what of the night?Watchman, what of the night?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Proclamation Against Arabia'
      title: Proclamation Against Arabia
      number: 12
      content: "The watchman said,\u201CThe morning comes, and also the night.If
        you will inquire, inquire;Return! Come back!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: The burden against Arabia.In the forest in Arabia you will lodge,O
        you traveling companies of Dedanites.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: O inhabitants of the land of Tema,Bring water to him who is thirsty;With
        their bread they met him who fled.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: For they fled from the swords, from the drawn sword,From the bent
        bow, and from the distress of war.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "For thus the Lord has said to me: \u201CWithin a year, according
        to the year of a hired man, all the glory of Kedar will fail; "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "and the remainder of the number of archers, the mighty men of the
        people of Kedar, will be diminished; for the Lord God of Israel has spoken
        it.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Proclamation Against Jerusalem'
      title: Proclamation Against Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: The burden against the Valley of Vision.What ails you now, that you
        have all gone up to the housetops,
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: You who are full of noise,A tumultuous city, a joyous city?Your slain
        men  are not slain with the sword,Nor dead in battle.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: All your rulers have fled together;They are captured by the archers.All
        who are found in you are bound together;They have fled from afar.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Therefore I said, \u201CLook away from me,I will weep bitterly;Do
        not labor to comfort meBecause of the plundering of the daughter of my people.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For it  is a day of trouble and treading down and perplexityBy the
        Lord God of hostsIn the Valley of Vision\u2014Breaking down the wallsAnd
        of crying to the mountain."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Elam bore the quiverWith chariots of men and horsemen,And Kir uncovered
        the shield.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: It shall come to pass that your choicest valleysShall be full of chariots,And
        the horsemen shall set themselves in array at the gate.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: He removed the protection of Judah.You looked in that day to the armor
        of the House of the Forest;
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: You also saw the damage to the city of David,That it was great;And
        you gathered together the waters of the lower pool.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: You numbered the houses of Jerusalem,And the houses you broke downTo
        fortify the wall.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: You also made a reservoir between the two wallsFor the water of the
        old pool.But you did not look to its Maker,Nor did you have respect for Him
        who fashioned it long ago.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: And in that day the Lord God of hostsCalled for weeping and for mourning,For
        baldness and for girding with sackcloth.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But instead, joy and gladness,Slaying oxen and killing sheep,Eating
        meat and drinking wine:\u201CLet us eat and drink, for tomorrow we die!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: The Judgment on Shebna'
      title: The Judgment on Shebna
      number: 14
      content: "Then it was revealed in my hearing by the Lord of hosts,\u201CSurely
        for this iniquity there will be no atonement for you,Even to your death,\u201D
        says the Lord God of hosts."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Thus says the Lord God of hosts:\u201CGo, proceed to this steward,To
        Shebna, who is over the house, and  say:"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u2018What have you here, and whom have you here,That you have hewn
        a sepulcher here,As he who hews himself a sepulcher on high,Who carves a
        tomb for himself in a rock?"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Indeed, the Lord will throw you away violently,O mighty man,And will
        surely seize you.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "He will surely turn violently and toss you like a ballInto a large
        country;There you shall die, and there your glorious chariotsShall  be the
        shame of your master\u2019s house."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: So I will drive you out of your office,And from your position he will
        pull you down.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u2018Then it shall be in that day,That I will call My servant Eliakim
        the son of Hilkiah;"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: I will clothe him with your robeAnd strengthen him with your belt;I
        will commit your responsibility into his hand.He shall be a father to the
        inhabitants of JerusalemAnd to the house of Judah.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: The key of the house of DavidI will lay on his shoulder;So he shall
        open, and no one shall shut;And he shall shut, and no one shall open.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "I will fasten him as  a peg in a secure place,And he will become
        a glorious throne to his father\u2019s house."
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u2018They will hang on him all the glory of his father\u2019s house,
        the offspring and the posterity, all vessels of small quantity, from the
        cups to all the pitchers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "In that day,\u2019 says the Lord of hosts, \u2018the peg that is
        fastened in the secure place will be removed and be cut down and fall, and
        the burden that was on it will be cut off; for the Lord has spoken.\u2019
        \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Proclamation Against Tyre'
      title: Proclamation Against Tyre
      number: 1
      content: The burden against Tyre.Wail, you ships of Tarshish!For it is laid
        waste,So that there is no house, no harbor;From the land of Cyprus it is
        revealed to them.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Be still, you inhabitants of the coastland,You merchants of Sidon,Whom
        those who cross the sea have filled.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: And on great waters the grain of Shihor,The harvest of the River,
        is her revenue;And she is a marketplace for the nations.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Be ashamed, O Sidon;For the sea has spoken,The strength of the sea,
        saying,\u201CI do not labor, nor bring forth children;Neither do I rear young
        men,Nor bring up virgins.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: When the report reaches Egypt,They also will be in agony at the report
        of Tyre.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Cross over to Tarshish;Wail, you inhabitants of the coastland!
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Is this your joyous city,Whose antiquity is from ancient days,Whose
        feet carried her far off to dwell?
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Who has taken this counsel against Tyre, the crowning city,Whose merchants
        are princes,Whose traders are the honorable of the earth?
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: The Lord of hosts has purposed it,To bring to dishonor the pride of
        all glory,To bring into contempt all the honorable of the earth.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Overflow through your land like the River,O daughter of Tarshish;There 
        is no more strength.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: He stretched out His hand over the sea,He shook the kingdoms;The Lord
        has given a commandment against CanaanTo destroy its strongholds.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And He said, \u201CYou will rejoice no more,O you oppressed virgin
        daughter of Sidon.Arise, cross over to Cyprus;There also you will have no
        rest.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Behold, the land of the Chaldeans,This people which was not;Assyria
        founded it for wild beasts of the desert.They set up its towers,They raised
        up its palaces,And brought it to ruin.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Wail, you ships of Tarshish!For your strength is laid waste.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now it shall come to pass in that day that Tyre will be forgotten
        seventy years, according to the days of one king. At the end of seventy years
        it will happen to Tyre as in the song of the harlot:'
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CTake a harp, go about the city,You forgotten harlot;Make sweet
        melody, sing many songs,That you may be remembered.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And it shall be, at the end of seventy years, that the Lord will
        deal with Tyre. She will return to her hire, and commit fornication with
        all the kingdoms of the world on the face of the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Her gain and her pay will be set apart for the Lord; it will not be
        treasured nor laid up, for her gain will be for those who dwell before the
        Lord, to eat sufficiently, and for fine clothing.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Impending Judgment on the Earth'
      title: Impending Judgment on the Earth
      number: 1
      content: Behold, the Lord makes the earth empty and makes it waste,Distorts
        its surfaceAnd scatters abroad its inhabitants.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: And it shall be:As with the people, so with the priest;As with the
        servant, so with his master;As with the maid, so with her mistress;As with
        the buyer, so with the seller;As with the lender, so with the borrower;As
        with the creditor, so with the debtor.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: The land shall be entirely emptied and utterly plundered,For the Lord
        has spoken this word.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: The earth mourns and fades away,The world languishes and fades away;The
        haughty people of the earth languish.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: The earth is also defiled under its inhabitants,Because they have
        transgressed the laws,Changed the ordinance,Broken the everlasting covenant.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Therefore the curse has devoured the earth,And those who dwell in
        it are desolate.Therefore the inhabitants of the earth are burned,And few
        men are left.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: The new wine fails, the vine languishes,All the merry-hearted sigh.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: The mirth of the tambourine ceases,The noise of the jubilant ends,The
        joy of the harp ceases.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: They shall not drink wine with a song;Strong drink is bitter to those
        who drink it.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: The city of confusion is broken down;Every house is shut up, so that
        none may go in.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: There  is a cry for wine in the streets,All joy is darkened,The mirth
        of the land is gone.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: In the city desolation is left,And the gate is stricken with destruction.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: When it shall be thus in the midst of the land among the people,It 
        shall  be like the shaking of an olive tree,Like the gleaning of grapes when
        the vintage is done.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: They shall lift up their voice, they shall sing;For the majesty of
        the LordThey shall cry aloud from the sea.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Therefore glorify the Lord in the dawning light,The name of the Lord
        God of Israel in the coastlands of the sea.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "From the ends of the earth we have heard songs:\u201CGlory to the
        righteous!\u201DBut I said, \u201CI am ruined, ruined!Woe to me!The treacherous
        dealers have dealt treacherously,Indeed, the treacherous dealers have dealt
        very treacherously.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Fear and the pit and the snareAre upon you, O inhabitant of the earth.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: And it shall beThat he who flees from the noise of the fearShall fall
        into the pit,And he who comes up from the midst of the pitShall be caught
        in the snare;For the windows from on high are open,And the foundations of
        the earth are shaken.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: The earth is violently broken,The earth is split open,The earth is
        shaken exceedingly.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: The earth shall reel to and fro like a drunkard,And shall totter like
        a hut;Its transgression shall be heavy upon it,And it will fall, and not
        rise again.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: It shall come to pass in that dayThat the Lord will punish on high
        the host of exalted ones,And on the earth the kings of the earth.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: They will be gathered together,As prisoners are gathered in the pit,And
        will be shut up in the prison;After many days they will be punished.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Then the moon will be disgracedAnd the sun ashamed;For the Lord of
        hosts will reignOn Mount Zion and in JerusalemAnd before His elders, gloriously.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Praise to God'
      title: Praise to God
      number: 1
      content: O Lord, You are my God.I will exalt You,I will praise Your name,For
        You have done wonderful things;Your counsels of old are faithfulness and
        truth.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: For You have made a city a ruin,A fortified city a ruin,A palace of
        foreigners to be a city no more;It will never be rebuilt.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Therefore the strong people will glorify You;The city of the terrible
        nations will fear You.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: For You have been a strength to the poor,A strength to the needy in
        his distress,A refuge from the storm,A shade from the heat;For the blast
        of the terrible ones is as a storm against the wall.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: You will reduce the noise of aliens,As heat in a dry place;As heat
        in the shadow of a cloud,The song of the terrible ones will be diminished.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: And in this mountainThe Lord of hosts will make for all peopleA feast
        of choice pieces,A feast of wines on the lees,Of fat things full of marrow,Of
        well-refined wines on the lees.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: And He will destroy on this mountainThe surface of the covering cast
        over all people,And the veil that is spread over all nations.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: He will swallow up death forever,And the Lord God will wipe away tears
        from all faces;The rebuke of His peopleHe will take away from all the earth;For
        the Lord has spoken.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And it will be said in that day:\u201CBehold, this is our God;We
        have waited for Him, and He will save us.This is the Lord;We have waited
        for Him;We will be glad and rejoice in His salvation.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: For on this mountain the hand of the Lord will rest,And Moab shall
        be trampled down under Him,As straw is trampled down for the refuse heap.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: And He will spread out His hands in their midstAs a swimmer reaches
        out to swim,And He will bring down their prideTogether with the trickery
        of their hands.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: The fortress of the high fort of your wallsHe will bring down, lay
        low,And bring to the ground, down to the dust.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Song of Salvation'
      title: A Song of Salvation
      number: 1
      content: "In that day this song will be sung in the land of Judah:\u201CWe
        have a strong city;God will appoint salvation for walls and bulwarks."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Open the gates,That the righteous nation which keeps the truth may
        enter in.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: You will keep him in perfect peace,Whose mind is stayed on  You,Because
        he trusts in You.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Trust in the Lord forever,For in YAH, the Lord, is everlasting strength.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: For He brings down those who dwell on high,The lofty city;He lays
        it low,He lays it low to the ground,He brings it down to the dust.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "The foot shall tread it down\u2014The feet of the poorAnd the steps
        of the needy.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: The way of the just is uprightness;O Most Upright,You weigh the path
        of the just.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Yes, in the way of Your judgments,O Lord, we have waited for You;The
        desire of our soul is for Your nameAnd for the remembrance of You.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: With my soul I have desired You in the night,Yes, by my spirit within
        me I will seek You early;For when Your judgments are in the earth,The inhabitants
        of the world will learn righteousness.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Let grace be shown to the wicked,Yet he will not learn righteousness;In
        the land of uprightness he will deal unjustly,And will not behold the majesty
        of the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Lord, when Your hand is lifted up, they will not see.But they will
        see and be ashamedFor their envy of people;Yes, the fire of Your enemies
        shall devour them.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Lord, You will establish peace for us,For You have also done all our
        works in us.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: O Lord our God, masters besides YouHave had dominion over us;But by
        You only we make mention of Your name.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: They  are dead, they will not live;They  are deceased, they will not
        rise.Therefore You have punished and destroyed them,And made all their memory
        to perish.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: You have increased the nation, O Lord,You have increased the nation;You
        are glorified;You have expanded all the borders of the land.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Lord, in trouble they have visited You,They poured out a prayer when
        Your chastening was upon them.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: As a woman with childIs in pain and cries out in her pangs,When she
        draws near the time of her delivery,So have we been in Your sight, O Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: We have been with child, we have been in pain;We have, as it were,
        brought forth wind;We have not accomplished any deliverance in the earth,Nor
        have the inhabitants of the world fallen.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Take Refuge from the Coming Judgment'
      title: Take Refuge from the Coming Judgment
      number: 19
      content: Your dead shall live;Together  with my dead body they shall arise.Awake
        and sing, you who dwell in dust;For your dew is  like the dew of herbs,And
        the earth shall cast out the dead.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Come, my people, enter your chambers,And shut your doors behind you;Hide
        yourself, as it were, for a little moment,Until the indignation is past.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: For behold, the Lord  comes out of His placeTo punish the inhabitants
        of the earth for their iniquity;The earth will also disclose her blood,And
        will no more cover her slain.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Restoration of Israel'
      title: The Restoration of Israel
      number: 1
      content: In that day the Lord with His severe sword, great and strong,Will
        punish Leviathan the fleeing serpent,Leviathan that twisted serpent;And He
        will slay the reptile that is in the sea.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "In that day sing to her,\u201CA vineyard of red wine!"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: I, the Lord, keep it,I water it every moment;Lest any hurt it,I keep
        it night and day.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Fury is not in Me.Who would set briers and thornsAgainst Me in battle?I
        would go through them,I would burn them together.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Or let him take hold of My strength,That he may make peace with Me;And
        he shall make peace with Me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Those who come He shall cause to take root in Jacob;Israel shall blossom
        and bud,And fill the face of the world with fruit.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Has He struck Israel as He struck those who struck him?Or has He been
        slain according to the slaughter of those who were slain by Him?
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: In measure, by sending it away,You contended with it.He removes it
        by His rough windIn the day of the east wind.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Therefore by this the iniquity of Jacob will be covered;And this is
        all the fruit of taking away his sin:When he makes all the stones of the
        altarLike chalkstones that are beaten to dust,Wooden images and incense altars
        shall not stand.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Yet the fortified city will  be  desolate,The habitation forsaken
        and left like a wilderness;There the calf will feed, and there it will lie
        downAnd consume its branches.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: When its boughs are withered, they will be broken off;The women come
        and set them on fire.For it is a people of no understanding;Therefore He
        who made them will not have mercy on them,And He who formed them will show
        them no favor.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: And it shall come to pass in that dayThat the Lord will thresh,From
        the channel of the River to the Brook of Egypt;And you will be gathered one
        by one,O you children of Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: So it shall be in that day:The great trumpet will be blown;They will
        come, who are about to perish in the land of Assyria,And they who are outcasts
        in the land of Egypt,And shall worship the Lord in the holy mount at Jerusalem.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Woe to Ephraim and Jerusalem'
      title: Woe to Ephraim and Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: Woe to the crown of pride, to the drunkards of Ephraim,Whose glorious
        beauty is a fading flowerWhich is at the head of the verdant valleys,To those
        who are overcome with wine!
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Behold, the Lord has a mighty and strong one,Like a tempest of hail
        and a destroying storm,Like a flood of mighty waters overflowing,Who will
        bring them down to the earth with His hand.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: The crown of pride, the drunkards of Ephraim,Will be trampled underfoot;
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: And the glorious beauty is a fading flowerWhich is at the head of
        the verdant valley,Like the first fruit before the summer,Which an observer
        sees;He eats it up while it is still in his hand.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: In that day the Lord of hosts will beFor a crown of glory and a diadem
        of beautyTo the remnant of His people,
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: For a spirit of justice to him who sits in judgment,And for strength
        to those who turn back the battle at the gate.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: But they also have erred through wine,And through intoxicating drink
        are out of the way;The priest and the prophet have erred through intoxicating
        drink,They are swallowed up by wine,They are out of the way through intoxicating
        drink;They err in vision, they stumble in judgment.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: For all tables are full of vomit and filth;No place is  clean.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CWhom will he teach knowledge?And whom will he make to understand
        the message?Those just weaned from milk?Those just drawn from the breasts?"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "For precept must  be upon precept, precept upon precept,Line upon
        line, line upon line,Here a little, there a little.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: For with stammering lips and another tongueHe will speak to this people,
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "To whom He said, \u201CThis is the rest with  whichYou may cause
        the weary to rest,\u201DAnd, \u201CThis is the refreshing\u201D;Yet they
        would not hear."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But the word of the Lord was to them,\u201CPrecept upon precept,
        precept upon precept,Line upon line, line upon line,Here a little, there
        a little,\u201DThat they might go and fall backward, and be brokenAnd snared
        and caught."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Therefore hear the word of the Lord, you scornful men,Who rule this
        people who are in Jerusalem,
      comments: []
    - name: '15: A Cornerstone in Zion'
      title: A Cornerstone in Zion
      number: 15
      content: "Because you have said, \u201CWe have made a covenant with death,And
        with Sheol we are in agreement.When the overflowing scourge passes through,It
        will not come to us,For we have made lies our refuge,And under falsehood
        we have hidden ourselves.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord God:\u201CBehold, I lay in Zion a stone
        for a foundation,A tried stone, a precious cornerstone, a sure foundation;Whoever
        believes will not act hastily."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Also I will make justice the measuring line,And righteousness the
        plummet;The hail will sweep away the refuge of lies,And the waters will overflow
        the hiding place.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Your covenant with death will be annulled,And your agreement with
        Sheol will not stand;When the overflowing scourge passes through,Then you
        will be trampled down by it.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "As often as it goes out it will take you;For morning by morning it
        will pass over,And by day and by night;It will be a terror just to understand
        the report.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: For the bed is too short to stretch out on,And the covering so narrow
        that one cannot wrap himself in  it.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "For the Lord will rise up as at Mount Perazim,He will be angry as
        in the Valley of Gibeon\u2014That He may do His work, His awesome work,And
        bring to pass His act, His unusual act."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Listen to the Teaching of God'
      title: Listen to the Teaching of God
      number: 22
      content: Now therefore, do not be mockers,Lest your bonds be made strong;For
        I have heard from the Lord God of hosts,A destruction determined even upon
        the whole earth.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Give ear and hear my voice,Listen and hear my speech.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: Does the plowman keep plowing all day to sow?Does he keep turning
        his soil and breaking the clods?
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: When he has leveled its surface,Does he not sow the black cumminAnd
        scatter the cummin,Plant the wheat in rows,The barley in the appointed place,And
        the spelt in its place?
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: For He instructs him in right judgment,His God teaches him.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: For the black cummin is not threshed with a threshing sledge,Nor is
        a cartwheel rolled over the cummin;But the black cummin is beaten out with
        a stick,And the cummin with a rod.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: Bread flour must be ground;Therefore he does not thresh it forever,Break
        it  with his cartwheel,Or crush it with his horsemen.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: This also comes from the Lord of hosts,Who is wonderful in counsel
        and excellent in guidance.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Woe to Jerusalem'
      title: Woe to Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CWoe to Ariel, to Ariel, the city where David dwelt!Add year
        to year;Let feasts come around."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Yet I will distress Ariel;There shall be heaviness and sorrow,And
        it shall be to Me as Ariel.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: I will encamp against you all around,I will lay siege against you
        with a mound,And I will raise siegeworks against you.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "You shall be brought down,You shall speak out of the ground;Your
        speech shall be low, out of the dust;Your voice shall be like a medium\u2019s,
        out of the ground;And your speech shall whisper out of the dust."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CMoreover the multitude of your foesShall be like fine dust,And
        the multitude of the terrible onesLike chaff that passes away;Yes, it shall
        be in an instant, suddenly."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: You will be punished by the Lord of hostsWith thunder and earthquake
        and great noise,With storm and tempestAnd the flame of devouring fire.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: The multitude of all the nations who fight against Ariel,Even all
        who fight against her and her fortress,And distress her,Shall be as a dream
        of a night vision.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: The Blindness of Disobedience'
      title: The Blindness of Disobedience
      number: 8
      content: "It shall even be as when a hungry man dreams,And look\u2014he eats;But
        he awakes, and his soul is still empty;Or as when a thirsty man dreams,And
        look\u2014he drinks;But he awakes, and indeed he  is faint,And his soul still
        craves:So the multitude of all the nations shall be,Who fight against Mount
        Zion.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Pause and wonder!Blind yourselves and be blind!They are drunk, but
        not with wine;They stagger, but not with intoxicating drink.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: For the Lord has poured out on youThe spirit of deep sleep,And has
        closed your eyes, namely, the prophets;And He has covered your heads, namely, 
        the seers.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "The whole vision has become to you like the words of a book that
        is sealed, which men deliver to one who is literate, saying, \u201CRead this,
        please.\u201DAnd he says, \u201CI cannot, for it is sealed.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then the book is delivered to one who is illiterate, saying, \u201CRead
        this, please.\u201DAnd he says, \u201CI am not literate.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Therefore the Lord said:\u201CInasmuch as these people draw near
        with their mouthsAnd honor Me with their lips,But have removed their hearts
        far from Me,And their fear toward Me is taught by the commandment of men,"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Therefore, behold, I will again do a marvelous workAmong this people,A
        marvelous work and a wonder;For the wisdom of their wise men shall perish,And
        the understanding of their prudent men shall be hidden.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Woe to those who seek deep to hide their counsel far from the Lord,And
        their works are in the dark;They say, \u201CWho sees us?\u201D and, \u201CWho
        knows us?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Future Recovery of Wisdom'
      title: Future Recovery of Wisdom
      number: 16
      content: "Surely you have things turned around!Shall the potter be esteemed
        as the clay;For shall the thing made say of him who made it,\u201CHe did
        not make me\u201D?Or shall the thing formed say of him who formed it,\u201CHe
        has no understanding\u201D?"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Is it not yet a very little whileTill Lebanon shall be turned into
        a fruitful field,And the fruitful field be esteemed as a forest?
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: In that day the deaf shall hear the words of the book,And the eyes
        of the blind shall see out of obscurity and out of darkness.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: The humble also shall increase their joy in the Lord,And the poor
        among men shall rejoiceIn the Holy One of Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "For the terrible one is brought to nothing,The scornful one is consumed,And
        all who watch for iniquity are cut off\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Who make a man an offender by a word,And lay a snare for him who reproves
        in the gate,And turn aside the just by empty words.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord, who redeemed Abraham, concerning the
        house of Jacob:\u201CJacob shall not now be ashamed,Nor shall his face now
        grow pale;"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: But when he sees his children,The work of My hands, in his midst,They
        will hallow My name,And hallow the Holy One of Jacob,And fear the God of
        Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "These also who erred in spirit will come to understanding,And those
        who complained will learn doctrine.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Futile Confidence in Egypt'
      title: Futile Confidence in Egypt
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CWoe to the rebellious children,\u201D says the Lord,\u201CWho
        take counsel, but not of Me,And who devise plans, but not of My Spirit,That
        they may add sin to sin;"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Who walk to go down to Egypt,And have not asked My advice,To strengthen
        themselves in the strength of Pharaoh,And to trust in the shadow of Egypt!
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Therefore the strength of PharaohShall be your shame,And trust in
        the shadow of EgyptShall be your humiliation.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: For his princes were at Zoan,And his ambassadors came to Hanes.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "They were all ashamed of a people who could not benefit them,Or be
        help or benefit,But a shame and also a reproach.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: The burden against the beasts of the South.Through a land of trouble
        and anguish,From which came the lioness and lion,The viper and fiery flying
        serpent,They will carry their riches on the backs of young donkeys,And their
        treasures on the humps of camels,To a people who shall not profit;
      comments: []
    - name: '7: A Rebellious People'
      title: A Rebellious People
      number: 7
      content: For the Egyptians shall help in vain and to no purpose.Therefore I
        have called herRahab-Hem-Shebeth.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now go, write it before them on a tablet,And note it on a scroll,That
        it may be for time to come,Forever and ever:'
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: That this is a rebellious people,Lying children,Children who will
        not hear the law of the Lord;
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Who say to the seers, \u201CDo not see,\u201DAnd to the prophets,
        \u201CDo not prophesy to us right things;Speak to us smooth things, prophesy
        deceits."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Get out of the way,Turn aside from the path,Cause the Holy One of
        IsraelTo cease from before us.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Therefore thus says the Holy One of Israel:\u201CBecause you despise
        this word,And trust in oppression and perversity,And rely on them,"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Therefore this iniquity shall be to youLike a breach ready to fall,A
        bulge in a high wall,Whose breaking comes suddenly, in an instant.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And He shall break it like the breaking of the potter\u2019s vessel,Which
        is broken in pieces;He shall not spare.So there shall not be found among
        its fragmentsA shard to take fire from the hearth,Or to take water from the
        cistern.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "For thus says the Lord God, the Holy One of Israel:\u201CIn returning
        and rest you shall be saved;In quietness and confidence shall be your strength.\u201DBut
        you would not,"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And you said, \u201CNo, for we will flee on horses\u201D\u2014Therefore
        you shall flee!And, \u201CWe will ride on swift horses\u201D\u2014Therefore
        those who pursue you shall be swift!"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: God Will Be Gracious'
      title: God Will Be Gracious
      number: 17
      content: One thousand shall  flee at the threat of one,At the threat of five
        you shall flee,Till you are left as a pole on top of a mountainAnd as a banner
        on a hill.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Therefore the Lord will wait, that He may be gracious to you;And therefore
        He will be exalted, that He may have mercy on you.For the Lord  is a God
        of justice;Blessed are all those who wait for Him.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: For the people shall dwell in Zion at Jerusalem;You shall weep no
        more.He will be very gracious to you at the sound of your cry;When He hears
        it, He will answer you.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: And though the Lord gives youThe bread of adversity and the water
        of affliction,Yet your teachers will not be moved into a corner anymore,But
        your eyes shall see your teachers.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Your ears shall hear a word behind you, saying,\u201CThis is the
        way, walk in it,\u201DWhenever you turn to the right handOr whenever you
        turn to the left."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "You will also defile the covering of your images of silver,And the
        ornament of your molded images of gold.You will throw them away as an unclean
        thing;You will say to them, \u201CGet away!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Then He will give the rain for your seedWith which you sow the ground,And
        bread of the increase of the earth;It will be fat and plentiful.In that day
        your cattle will feedIn large pastures.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: Likewise the oxen and the young donkeys that work the groundWill eat
        cured fodder,Which has been winnowed with the shovel and fan.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: There will be on every high mountainAnd on every high hillRivers and
        streams of waters,In the day of the great slaughter,When the towers fall.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: Judgment on Assyria'
      title: Judgment on Assyria
      number: 26
      content: Moreover the light of the moon will be as the light of the sun,And
        the light of the sun will be sevenfold,As the light of seven days,In the
        day that the Lord binds up the bruise of His peopleAnd heals the stroke of
        their wound.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Behold, the name of the Lord comes from afar,Burning with His anger,And
        His burden is heavy;His lips are full of indignation,And His tongue like
        a devouring fire.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: His breath is like an overflowing stream,Which reaches up to the neck,To
        sift the nations with the sieve of futility;And there  shall  be  a bridle
        in the jaws of the people,Causing them to err.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: You shall have a songAs in the night when a holy festival is kept,And
        gladness of heart as when one goes with a flute,To come into the mountain
        of the Lord,To the Mighty One of Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: The Lord will cause His glorious voice to be heard,And show the descent
        of His arm,With the indignation of His angerAnd the flame of a devouring
        fire,With scattering, tempest, and hailstones.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: For through the voice of the LordAssyria will be beaten down,As He
        strikes with the rod.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: And in every place where the staff of punishment passes,Which the
        Lord lays on him,It will be with tambourines and harps;And in battles of
        brandishing He will fight with it.
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: For Tophet was established of old,Yes, for the king it is prepared.He
        has made it deep and large;Its pyre is fire with much wood;The breath of
        the Lord, like a stream of brimstone,Kindles it.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Folly of Not Trusting God'
      title: The Folly of Not Trusting God
      number: 1
      content: Woe to those who go down to Egypt for help,And  rely on horses,Who
        trust in chariots because they  are many,And in horsemen because they are
        very strong,But who do not look to the Holy One of Israel,Nor seek the Lord!
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Yet He also is wise and will bring disaster,And will not call back
        His words,But will arise against the house of evildoers,And against the help
        of those who work iniquity.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: God Will Deliver Jerusalem'
      title: God Will Deliver Jerusalem
      number: 3
      content: Now the Egyptians are men, and not God;And their horses are flesh,
        and not spirit.When the Lord stretches out His hand,Both he who helps will
        fall,And he who is helped will fall down;They all will perish together.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For thus the Lord has spoken to me:\u201CAs a lion roars,And a young
        lion over his prey(When a multitude of shepherds is summoned against him,He
        will not be afraid of their voiceNor be disturbed by their noise),So the
        Lord of hosts will come downTo fight for Mount Zion and for its hill."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Like birds flying about,So will the Lord of hosts defend Jerusalem.Defending,
        He will also deliver it;Passing over, He will preserve it.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Return to  Him against whom the children of Israel have deeply revolted. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "For in that day every man shall throw away his idols of silver and
        his idols of gold\u2014sin, which your own hands have made for yourselves."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CThen Assyria shall fall by a sword not of man,And a sword not
        of mankind shall devour him.But he shall flee from the sword,And his young
        men shall become forced labor."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "He shall cross over to his stronghold for fear,And his princes shall
        be afraid of the banner,\u201DSays the Lord,Whose fire is in ZionAnd whose
        furnace is in Jerusalem."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Reign of Righteousness'
      title: A Reign of Righteousness
      number: 1
      content: Behold, a king will reign in righteousness,And princes will rule with
        justice.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: A man will be as a hiding place from the wind,And a cover from the
        tempest,As rivers of water in a dry place,As the shadow of a great rock in
        a weary land.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: The eyes of those who see will not be dim,And the ears of those who
        hear will listen.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Also the heart of the rash will understand knowledge,And the tongue
        of the stammerers will be ready to speak plainly.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: The foolish person will no longer be called generous,Nor the miser
        said to  be bountiful;
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: For the foolish person will speak foolishness,And his heart will work
        iniquity:To practice ungodliness,To utter error against the Lord,To keep
        the hungry unsatisfied,And he will cause the drink of the thirsty to fail.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Also the schemes of the schemer are evil;He devises wicked plansTo
        destroy the poor with lying words,Even when the needy speaks justice.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Consequences of Complacency'
      title: Consequences of Complacency
      number: 8
      content: But a generous man devises generous things,And by generosity he shall
        stand.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Rise up, you women who are at ease,Hear my voice;You complacent daughters,Give
        ear to my speech.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: In a year and some daysYou will be troubled, you complacent women;For
        the vintage will fail,The gathering will not come.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Tremble, you women who are at ease;Be troubled, you complacent ones;Strip
        yourselves, make yourselves bare,And gird sackcloth on your waists.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: People shall mourn upon their breastsFor the pleasant fields, for
        the fruitful vine.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: On the land of my people will come up thorns and briers,Yes, on all
        the happy homes in  the joyous city;
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Because the palaces will be forsaken,The bustling city will be deserted.The
        forts and towers will become lairs forever,A joy of wild donkeys, a pasture
        of flocks\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: "15: The Peace of God\u2019s Reign"
      title: "The Peace of God\u2019s Reign"
      number: 15
      content: Until the Spirit is poured upon us from on high,And the wilderness
        becomes a fruitful field,And the fruitful field is counted as a forest.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Then justice will dwell in the wilderness,And righteousness remain
        in the fruitful field.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: The work of righteousness will be peace,And the effect of righteousness,
        quietness and assurance forever.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: My people will dwell in a peaceful habitation,In secure dwellings,
        and in quiet resting places,
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Though hail comes down on the forest,And the city is brought low in
        humiliation.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Blessed are you who sow beside all waters,Who send out freely the
        feet of the ox and the donkey.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Prayer in Deep Distress'
      title: A Prayer in Deep Distress
      number: 1
      content: Woe to you who plunder, though you have not been plundered;And you
        who deal treacherously, though they have not dealt treacherously with you!When
        you cease plundering,You will be plundered;When you make an end of dealing
        treacherously,They will deal treacherously with you.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: O Lord, be gracious to us;We have waited for You.Be their arm every
        morning,Our salvation also in the time of trouble.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: At the noise of the tumult the people shall flee;When You lift Yourself
        up, the nations shall be scattered;
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: And Your plunder shall be gatheredLike the gathering of the caterpillar;As
        the running to and fro of locusts,He shall run upon them.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: The Lord is exalted, for He dwells on high;He has filled Zion with
        justice and righteousness.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Wisdom and knowledge will be the stability of your times,And the strength
        of salvation;The fear of the Lord  is His treasure.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Surely their valiant ones shall cry outside,The ambassadors of peace
        shall weep bitterly.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: The highways lie waste,The traveling man ceases.He has broken the
        covenant,He has despised the cities,He regards no man.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Impending Judgment on Zion'
      title: Impending Judgment on Zion
      number: 9
      content: The earth mourns and languishes,Lebanon is shamed and shriveled;Sharon
        is like a wilderness,And Bashan and Carmel shake off their  fruits.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CNow I will rise,\u201D says the Lord;\u201CNow I will be exalted,Now
        I will lift Myself up."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: You shall conceive chaff,You shall bring forth stubble;Your breath,
        as fire, shall devour you.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: And the people shall be like the burnings of lime;Like thorns cut
        up they shall be burned in the fire.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Hear, you who  are afar off, what I have done;And you who  are near,
        acknowledge My might.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "The sinners in Zion are afraid;Fearfulness has seized the hypocrites:\u201CWho
        among us shall dwell with the devouring fire?Who among us shall dwell with
        everlasting burnings?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He who walks righteously and speaks uprightly,He who despises the
        gain of oppressions,Who gestures with his hands, refusing bribes,Who stops
        his ears from hearing of bloodshed,And shuts his eyes from seeing evil:'
      comments: []
    - name: '16: The Land of the Majestic King'
      title: The Land of the Majestic King
      number: 16
      content: He will dwell on high;His place of defense will  be the fortress of
        rocks;Bread will be given him,His water will  be sure.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Your eyes will see the King in His beauty;They will see the land that
        is very far off.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Your heart will meditate on terror:\u201CWhere is the scribe?Where
        is he who weighs?Where is he who counts the towers?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: You will not see a fierce people,A people of obscure speech, beyond
        perception,Of a stammering tongue that  you cannot understand.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Look upon Zion, the city of our appointed feasts;Your eyes will see
        Jerusalem, a quiet home,A tabernacle that will not be taken down;Not one
        of its stakes will ever be removed,Nor will any of its cords be broken.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: But there the majestic Lord  will  be for usA place of broad rivers
        and streams,In which no galley with oars will sail,Nor majestic ships pass
        by
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: (For the Lord  is our Judge,The Lord  is our Lawgiver,The Lord  is
        our King;He will save us);
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Your tackle is loosed,They could not strengthen their mast,They could
        not spread the sail.Then the prey of great plunder is divided;The lame take
        the prey.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And the inhabitant will not say, \u201CI am sick\u201D;The people
        who dwell in it will  be forgiven their iniquity."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judgment on the Nations'
      title: Judgment on the Nations
      number: 1
      content: Come near, you nations, to hear;And heed, you people!Let the earth
        hear, and all that is in it,The world and all things that come forth from
        it.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: For the indignation of the Lord is against all nations,And His fury
        against all their armies;He has utterly destroyed them,He has given them
        over to the slaughter.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Also their slain shall be thrown out;Their stench shall rise from
        their corpses,And the mountains shall be melted with their blood.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: All the host of heaven shall be dissolved,And the heavens shall be
        rolled up like a scroll;All their host shall fall downAs the leaf falls from
        the vine,And as fruit falling from a fig tree.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CFor My sword shall be bathed in heaven;Indeed it shall come
        down on Edom,And on the people of My curse, for judgment."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: The sword of the Lord is filled with blood,It is made overflowing
        with fatness,With the blood of lambs and goats,With the fat of the kidneys
        of rams.For the Lord has a sacrifice in Bozrah,And a great slaughter in the
        land of Edom.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The wild oxen shall come down with them,And the young bulls with
        the mighty bulls;Their land shall be soaked with blood,And their dust saturated
        with fatness.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "For it  is the day of the Lord\u2019s vengeance,The year of recompense
        for the cause of Zion."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Its streams shall be turned into pitch,And its dust into brimstone;Its
        land shall become burning pitch.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: It shall not be quenched night or day;Its smoke shall ascend forever.From
        generation to generation it shall lie waste;No one shall pass through it
        forever and ever.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: But the pelican and the porcupine shall possess it,Also the owl and
        the raven shall dwell in it.And He shall stretch out over itThe line of confusion
        and the stones of emptiness.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: They shall call its nobles to the kingdom,But none shall  be there,
        and all its princes shall be nothing.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: And thorns shall come up in its palaces,Nettles and brambles in its
        fortresses;It shall be a habitation of jackals,A courtyard for ostriches.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: The wild beasts of the desert shall also meet with the jackals,And
        the wild goat shall bleat to its companion;Also the night creature shall
        rest there,And find for herself a place of rest.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: There the arrow snake shall make her nest and lay eggsAnd hatch, and
        gather them under her shadow;There also shall the hawks be gathered,Every
        one with her mate.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CSearch from the book of the Lord, and read:Not one of these
        shall fail;Not one shall lack her mate.For My mouth has commanded it, and
        His Spirit has gathered them."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "He has cast the lot for them,And His hand has divided it among them
        with a measuring line.They shall possess it forever;From generation to generation
        they shall dwell in it.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Future Glory of Zion'
      title: The Future Glory of Zion
      number: 1
      content: The wilderness and the wasteland shall be glad for them,And the desert
        shall rejoice and blossom as the rose;
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: It shall blossom abundantly and rejoice,Even with joy and singing.The
        glory of Lebanon shall be given to it,The excellence of Carmel and Sharon.They
        shall see the glory of the Lord,The excellency of our God.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Strengthen the weak hands,And make firm the feeble knees.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Say to those who  are fearful-hearted,\u201CBe strong, do not fear!Behold,
        your God will come with  vengeance,With the recompense of God;He will come
        and save you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Then the eyes of the blind shall be opened,And the ears of the deaf
        shall be unstopped.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Then the lame shall leap like a deer,And the tongue of the dumb sing.For
        waters shall burst forth in the wilderness,And streams in the desert.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: The parched ground shall become a pool,And the thirsty land springs
        of water;In the habitation of jackals, where each lay,There  shall  be grass
        with reeds and rushes.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: A highway shall be there, and a road,And it shall be called the Highway
        of Holiness.The unclean shall not pass over it,But it shall  be for others.Whoever
        walks the road, although a fool,Shall not go astray.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: No lion shall be there,Nor shall any ravenous beast go up on it;It
        shall not be found there.But the redeemed shall walk there,
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: And the ransomed of the Lord shall return,And come to Zion with singing,With
        everlasting joy on their heads.They shall obtain joy and gladness,And sorrow
        and sighing shall flee away.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Sennacherib Boasts Against the Lord'
      title: Sennacherib Boasts Against the Lord
      number: 1
      content: 'Now it came to pass in the fourteenth year of King Hezekiah that
        Sennacherib king of Assyria came up against all the fortified cities of Judah
        and took them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then the king of Assyria sent the Rabshakeh with a great army from
        Lachish to King Hezekiah at Jerusalem. And he stood by the aqueduct from
        the upper pool, on the highway to the Fuller\u2019s Field. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: And Eliakim the son of Hilkiah, who was over the household, Shebna
        the scribe, and Joah the son of Asaph, the recorder, came out to him.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then the Rabshakeh said to them, \u201CSay now to Hezekiah, \u2018Thus
        says the great king, the king of Assyria: \u201CWhat confidence is this in
        which you trust? "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I say you speak of having plans and power for war; but they  are
        mere words. Now in whom do you trust, that you rebel against me? '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Look! You are trusting in the staff of this broken reed, Egypt, on
        which if a man leans, it will go into his hand and pierce it. So is Pharaoh
        king of Egypt to all who trust in him.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CBut if you say to me, \u2018We trust in the Lord our God,\u2019
        is  it not He whose high places and whose altars Hezekiah has taken away,
        and said to Judah and Jerusalem, \u2018You shall worship before this altar\u2019?\u201D
        \u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Now therefore, I urge you, give a pledge to my master the king of
        Assyria, and I will give you two thousand horses\u2014if you are able on
        your part to put riders on them! "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "How then will you repel one captain of the least of my master\u2019s
        servants, and put your trust in Egypt for chariots and horsemen? "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Have I now come up without the Lord against this land to destroy
        it? The Lord said to me, \u2018Go up against this land, and destroy it.\u2019
        \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Eliakim, Shebna, and Joah said to the Rabshakeh, \u201CPlease
        speak to your servants in Aramaic, for we understand it; and do not speak
        to us in Hebrew in the hearing of the people who are on the wall.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But the Rabshakeh said, \u201CHas my master sent me to your master
        and to you to speak these words, and not to the men who sit on the wall,
        who will eat and drink their own waste with you?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then the Rabshakeh stood and called out with a loud voice in Hebrew,
        and said, \u201CHear the words of the great king, the king of Assyria! "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Thus says the king: \u2018Do not let Hezekiah deceive you, for he
        will not be able to deliver you; "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "nor let Hezekiah make you trust in the Lord, saying, \u201CThe Lord
        will surely deliver us; this city will not be given into the hand of the
        king of Assyria.\u201D \u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Do not listen to Hezekiah; for thus says the king of Assyria: \u2018Make
        peace with me by  a present and come out to me; and every one of you eat
        from his own vine and every one from his own fig tree, and every one of you
        drink the waters of his own cistern; "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'until I come and take you away to a land like your own land, a land
        of grain and new wine, a land of bread and vineyards. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Beware lest Hezekiah persuade you, saying, \u201CThe Lord will deliver
        us.\u201D Has any one of the gods of the nations delivered its land from
        the hand of the king of Assyria? "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Where are the gods of Hamath and Arpad? Where are the gods of Sepharvaim?
        Indeed, have they delivered Samaria from my hand? '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Who among all the gods of these lands have delivered their countries
        from my hand, that the Lord should deliver Jerusalem from my hand?\u2019
        \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But they held their peace and answered him not a word; for the king\u2019s
        commandment was, \u201CDo not answer him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Then Eliakim the son of Hilkiah, who was over the household, Shebna
        the scribe, and Joah the son of Asaph, the recorder, came to Hezekiah with
        their clothes torn, and told him the words of the Rabshakeh.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Isaiah Assures Deliverance'
      title: Isaiah Assures Deliverance
      number: 1
      content: 'And so it was, when King Hezekiah heard it, that he tore his clothes,
        covered himself with sackcloth, and went into the house of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then he sent Eliakim, who was over the household, Shebna the scribe,
        and the elders of the priests, covered with sackcloth, to Isaiah the prophet,
        the son of Amoz. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And they said to him, \u201CThus says Hezekiah: \u2018This day is
        a day of trouble and rebuke and blasphemy; for the children have come to
        birth, but there  is no strength to bring them forth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "It may be that the Lord your God will hear the words of the Rabshakeh,
        whom his master the king of Assyria has sent to reproach the living God,
        and will rebuke the words which the Lord your God has heard. Therefore lift
        up your prayer for the remnant that is left.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So the servants of King Hezekiah came to Isaiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And Isaiah said to them, \u201CThus you shall say to your master,
        \u2018Thus says the Lord: \u201CDo not be afraid of the words which you have
        heard, with which the servants of the king of Assyria have blasphemed Me. "
      comments: []
    - name: "7: Sennacherib\u2019s Threat and Hezekiah\u2019s Prayer"
      title: "Sennacherib\u2019s Threat and Hezekiah\u2019s Prayer"
      number: 7
      content: "Surely I will send a spirit upon him, and he shall hear a rumor and
        return to his own land; and I will cause him to fall by the sword in his
        own land.\u201D \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then the Rabshakeh returned, and found the king of Assyria warring
        against Libnah, for he heard that he had departed from Lachish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And the king heard concerning Tirhakah king of Ethiopia, \u201CHe
        has come out to make war with you.\u201D So when he heard it, he sent messengers
        to Hezekiah, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CThus you shall speak to Hezekiah king of Judah, saying: \u2018Do
        not let your God in whom you trust deceive you, saying, \u201CJerusalem shall
        not be given into the hand of the king of Assyria.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Look! You have heard what the kings of Assyria have done to all lands
        by utterly destroying them; and shall you be delivered? '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Have the gods of the nations delivered those whom my fathers have
        destroyed, Gozan and Haran and Rezeph, and the people of Eden who were in
        Telassar? '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Where is the king of Hamath, the king of Arpad, and the king of the
        city of Sepharvaim, Hena, and Ivah?\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And Hezekiah received the letter from the hand of the messengers,
        and read it; and Hezekiah went up to the house of the Lord, and spread it
        before the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then Hezekiah prayed to the Lord, saying: '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CO Lord of hosts, God of Israel, the  One who dwells between
        the cherubim, You are God, You alone, of all the kingdoms of the earth. You
        have made heaven and earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Incline Your ear, O Lord, and hear; open Your eyes, O Lord, and see;
        and hear all the words of Sennacherib, which he has sent to reproach the
        living God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Truly, Lord, the kings of Assyria have laid waste all the nations
        and their lands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "and have cast their gods into the fire; for they were  not gods,
        but the work of men\u2019s hands\u2014wood and stone. Therefore they destroyed
        them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: The Word of the Lord Concerning Sennacherib'
      title: The Word of the Lord Concerning Sennacherib
      number: 20
      content: "Now therefore, O Lord our God, save us from his hand, that all the
        kingdoms of the earth may know that You are the Lord, You alone.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Isaiah the son of Amoz sent to Hezekiah, saying, \u201CThus
        says the Lord God of Israel, \u2018Because you have prayed to Me against
        Sennacherib king of Assyria, "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "this is the word which the Lord has spoken concerning him:\u201CThe
        virgin, the daughter of Zion,Has despised you, laughed you to scorn;The daughter
        of JerusalemHas shaken her head behind your back!"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CWhom have you reproached and blasphemed?Against whom have you
        raised your voice,And lifted up your eyes on high?Against the Holy One of
        Israel."
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "By your servants you have reproached the Lord,And said, \u2018By
        the multitude of my chariotsI have come up to the height of the mountains,To
        the limits of Lebanon;I will cut down its tall cedarsAnd its choice cypress
        trees;I will enter its farthest height,To its fruitful forest."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "I have dug and drunk water,And with the soles of my feet I have dried
        upAll the brooks of defense.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CDid you not hear long agoHow I made it,From ancient times that
        I formed it?Now I have brought it to pass,That you should beFor crushing
        fortified cities into heaps of ruins."
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Therefore their inhabitants had little power;They were dismayed and
        confounded;They were as the grass of the fieldAnd the green herb,As the grass
        on the housetopsAnd grain blighted before it is grown.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CBut I know your dwelling place,Your going out and your coming
        in,And your rage against Me."
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Because your rage against Me and your tumultHave come up to My ears,Therefore
        I will put My hook in your noseAnd My bridle in your lips,And I will turn
        you backBy the way which you came.\u201D \u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CThis shall  be a sign to you:You shall eat this year such as
        grows of itself,And the second year what springs from the same;Also in the
        third year sow and reap,Plant vineyards and eat the fruit of them."
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: And the remnant who have escaped of the house of JudahShall again
        take root downward,And bear fruit upward.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: For out of Jerusalem shall go a remnant,And those who escape from
        Mount Zion.The zeal of the Lord of hosts will do this.
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "\u201CTherefore thus says the Lord concerning the king of Assyria:\u2018He
        shall not come into this city,Nor shoot an arrow there,Nor come before it
        with shield,Nor build a siege mound against it."
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "By the way that he came,By the same shall he return;And he shall
        not come into this city,\u2019Says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: "35: Sennacherib\u2019s Defeat and Death"
      title: "Sennacherib\u2019s Defeat and Death"
      number: 35
      content: "\u2018For I will defend this city, to save itFor My own sake and
        for My servant David\u2019s sake.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Then the angel of the Lord went out, and killed in the camp of the
        Assyrians one hundred and eighty-five thousand; and when people arose early
        in the morning, there were the corpses\u2014all dead. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'So Sennacherib king of Assyria departed and went away, returned home,
        and remained at Nineveh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: Now it came to pass, as he was worshiping in the house of Nisroch
        his god, that his sons Adrammelech and Sharezer struck him down with the
        sword; and they escaped into the land of Ararat. Then Esarhaddon his son
        reigned in his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Hezekiah\u2019s Life Extended"
      title: "Hezekiah\u2019s Life Extended"
      number: 1
      content: "In those days Hezekiah was sick and near death. And Isaiah the prophet,
        the son of Amoz, went to him and said to him, \u201CThus says the Lord: \u2018Set
        your house in order, for you shall die and not live.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then Hezekiah turned his face toward the wall, and prayed to the
        Lord, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and said, \u201CRemember now, O Lord, I pray, how I have walked before
        You in truth and with a loyal heart, and have done what  is good in Your
        sight.\u201D And Hezekiah wept bitterly."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And the word of the Lord came to Isaiah, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CGo and tell Hezekiah, \u2018Thus says the Lord, the God of
        David your father: \u201CI have heard your prayer, I have seen your tears;
        surely I will add to your days fifteen years. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "I will deliver you and this city from the hand of the king of Assyria,
        and I will defend this city.\u201D \u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And this is  the sign to you from the Lord, that the Lord will do
        this thing which He has spoken: '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CBehold, I will bring the shadow on the sundial, which has gone
        down with the sun on the sundial of Ahaz, ten degrees backward.\u201D So
        the sun returned ten degrees on the dial by which it had gone down."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'This is the writing of Hezekiah king of Judah, when he had been sick
        and had recovered from his sickness:'
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "I said,\u201CIn the prime of my lifeI shall go to the gates of Sheol;I
        am deprived of the remainder of my years.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "I said,\u201CI shall not see Yah,The Lord  in the land of the living;I
        shall observe man no more among the inhabitants of the world."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "My life span is gone,Taken from me like a shepherd\u2019s tent;I
        have cut off my life like a weaver.He cuts me off from the loom;From day
        until night You make an end of me."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "I have considered until morning\u2014Like a lion,So He breaks all
        my bones;From day until night You make an end of me."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Like a crane or a swallow, so I chattered;I mourned like a dove;My
        eyes fail from  looking upward.O Lord, I am oppressed;Undertake for me!
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CWhat shall I say?He has both spoken to me,And He Himself has
        done it.I shall walk carefully all my yearsIn the bitterness of my soul."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: O Lord, by these things  men live;And in all these things  is the
        life of my spirit;So You will restore me and make me live.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Indeed it  was for my  own peaceThat I had great bitterness;But You
        have lovingly delivered my soul from the pit of corruption,For You have cast
        all my sins behind Your back.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: For Sheol cannot thank You,Death cannot praise You;Those who go down
        to the pit cannot hope for Your truth.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: The living, the living man, he shall praise You,As I do this day;The
        father shall make known Your truth to the children.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CThe Lord  was  ready to save me;Therefore we will sing my songs
        with stringed instrumentsAll the days of our life, in the house of the Lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Now Isaiah had said, \u201CLet them take a lump of figs, and apply
        it as a poultice on the boil, and he shall recover.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And Hezekiah had said, \u201CWhat is the sign that I shall go up
        to the house of the Lord?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Babylonian Envoys'
      title: The Babylonian Envoys
      number: 1
      content: 'At that time Merodach-Baladan the son of Baladan, king of Babylon,
        sent letters and a present to Hezekiah, for he heard that he had been sick
        and had recovered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Hezekiah was pleased with them, and showed them the house of
        his treasures\u2014the silver and gold, the spices and precious ointment,
        and all his armory\u2014all that was found among his treasures. There was
        nothing in his house or in all his dominion that Hezekiah did not show them."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Isaiah the prophet went to King Hezekiah, and said to him, \u201CWhat
        did these men say, and from where did they come to you?\u201DSo Hezekiah
        said, \u201CThey came to me from a far country, from Babylon.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And he said, \u201CWhat have they seen in your house?\u201DSo Hezekiah
        answered, \u201CThey have seen all that is in my house; there is nothing
        among my treasures that I have not shown them.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Isaiah said to Hezekiah, \u201CHear the word of the Lord of
        hosts: "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u2018Behold, the days are coming when all that is in your house,
        and what your fathers have accumulated until this day, shall be carried to
        Babylon; nothing shall be left,\u2019 says the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u2018And they shall take away some of your sons who will descend
        from you, whom you will beget; and they shall be eunuchs in the palace of
        the king of Babylon.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So Hezekiah said to Isaiah, \u201CThe word of the Lord which you
        have spoken is good!\u201D For he said, \u201CAt least there will be peace
        and truth in my days.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s People Are Comforted"
      title: "God\u2019s People Are Comforted"
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CComfort, yes, comfort My people!\u201DSays your God."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CSpeak comfort to Jerusalem, and cry out to her,That her warfare
        is ended,That her iniquity is pardoned;For she has received from the Lord\u2019s
        handDouble for all her sins.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "The voice of one crying in the wilderness:\u201CPrepare the way of
        the Lord;Make straight in the desertA highway for our God."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Every valley shall be exaltedAnd every mountain and hill brought low;The
        crooked places shall be made straightAnd the rough places smooth;
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "The glory of the Lord shall be revealed,And all flesh shall see it
        together;For the mouth of the Lord has spoken.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "The voice said, \u201CCry out!\u201DAnd he said, \u201CWhat shall
        I cry?\u201D\u201CAll flesh is grass,And all its loveliness is like the flower
        of the field."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: The grass withers, the flower fades,Because the breath of the Lord
        blows upon it;Surely the people are grass.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The grass withers, the flower fades,But the word of our God stands
        forever.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "O Zion,You who bring good tidings,Get up into the high mountain;O
        Jerusalem,You who bring good tidings,Lift up your voice with strength,Lift
        it up, be not afraid;Say to the cities of Judah, \u201CBehold your God!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Behold, the Lord God shall come with a strong hand,And His arm shall
        rule for Him;Behold, His reward is with Him,And His work before Him.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: He will feed His flock like a shepherd;He will gather the lambs with
        His arm,And carry them in His bosom,And gently lead those who are with young.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Who has measured the waters in the hollow of His hand,Measured heaven
        with a spanAnd calculated the dust of the earth in a measure?Weighed the
        mountains in scalesAnd the hills in a balance?
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Who has directed the Spirit of the Lord,Or as His counselor has taught
        Him?
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: With whom did He take counsel, and who instructed Him,And taught Him
        in the path of justice?Who taught Him knowledge,And showed Him the way of
        understanding?
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Behold, the nations are as a drop in a bucket,And are counted as the
        small dust on the scales;Look, He lifts up the isles as a very little thing.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: And Lebanon is not sufficient to burn,Nor its beasts sufficient for
        a burnt offering.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: All nations before Him are as nothing,And they are counted by Him
        less than nothing and worthless.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: To whom then will you liken God?Or what likeness will you compare
        to Him?
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: The workman molds an image,The goldsmith overspreads it with gold,And
        the silversmith casts silver chains.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Whoever is too impoverished for such a contributionChooses a tree
        that will not rot;He seeks for himself a skillful workmanTo prepare a carved
        image that will not totter.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Have you not known?Have you not heard?Has it not been told you from
        the beginning?Have you not understood from the foundations of the earth?
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: It  is He who sits above the circle of the earth,And its inhabitants
        are like grasshoppers,Who stretches out the heavens like a curtain,And spreads
        them out like a tent to dwell in.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: He brings the princes to nothing;He makes the judges of the earth
        useless.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: Scarcely shall they be planted,Scarcely shall they be sown,Scarcely
        shall their stock take root in the earth,When He will also blow on them,And
        they will wither,And the whirlwind will take them away like stubble.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CTo whom then will you liken Me,Or to  whom shall I be equal?\u201D
        says the Holy One."
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: Lift up your eyes on high,And see who has created these things,Who
        brings out their host by number;He calls them all by name,By the greatness
        of His mightAnd the strength of His power;Not one is missing.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Why do you say, O Jacob,And speak, O Israel:\u201CMy way is hidden
        from the Lord,And my just claim is passed over by my God\u201D?"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: Have you not known?Have you not heard?The everlasting God, the Lord,The
        Creator of the ends of the earth,Neither faints nor is weary.His understanding
        is unsearchable.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: He gives power to the weak,And to those  who  have no might He increases
        strength.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: Even the youths shall faint and be weary,And the young men shall utterly
        fall,
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: But those who wait on the LordShall renew their strength;They shall
        mount up with wings like eagles,They shall run and not be weary,They shall
        walk and not faint.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Israel Assured of God\u2019s Help"
      title: "Israel Assured of God\u2019s Help"
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CKeep silence before Me, O coastlands,And let the people renew
        their strength!Let them come near, then let them speak;Let us come near together
        for judgment."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CWho raised up one from the east?Who in righteousness called
        him to His feet?Who gave the nations before him,And made him rule over kings?Who
        gave them as the dust to his sword,As driven stubble to his bow?"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Who pursued them, and passed safelyBy the way that he had not gone
        with his feet?
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Who has performed and done it,Calling the generations from the beginning?\u2018I,
        the Lord, am the first;And with the last I am  He.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: The coastlands saw it and feared,The ends of the earth were afraid;They
        drew near and came.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Everyone helped his neighbor,And said to his brother,\u201CBe of
        good courage!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So the craftsman encouraged the goldsmith;He who smooths with the
        hammer inspired him who strikes the anvil,Saying, \u201CIt is ready for the
        soldering\u201D;Then he fastened it with pegs,That it might not totter."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CBut you, Israel, are My servant,Jacob whom I have chosen,The
        descendants of Abraham My friend."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "You whom I have taken from the ends of the earth,And called from
        its farthest regions,And said to you,\u2018You are My servant,I have chosen
        you and have not cast you away:"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Fear not, for I am with you;Be not dismayed, for I am your God.I
        will strengthen you,Yes, I will help you,I will uphold you with My righteous
        right hand.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CBehold, all those who were incensed against youShall be ashamed
        and disgraced;They shall be as nothing,And those who strive with you shall
        perish."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "You shall seek them and not find them\u2014Those who contended with
        you.Those who war against youShall be as nothing,As a nonexistent thing."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "For I, the Lord your God, will hold your right hand,Saying to you,
        \u2018Fear not, I will help you.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CFear not, you worm Jacob,You men of Israel!I will help you,\u201D
        says the LordAnd your Redeemer, the Holy One of Israel."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CBehold, I will make you into a new threshing sledge with sharp
        teeth;You shall thresh the mountains and beat them small,And make the hills
        like chaff."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: You shall winnow them, the wind shall carry them away,And the whirlwind
        shall scatter them;You shall rejoice in the Lord,And glory in the Holy One
        of Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CThe poor and needy seek water, but there  is none,Their tongues
        fail for thirst.I, the Lord, will hear them;I, the God of Israel, will not
        forsake them."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: I will open rivers in desolate heights,And fountains in the midst
        of the valleys;I will make the wilderness a pool of water,And the dry land
        springs of water.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: I will plant in the wilderness the cedar and the acacia tree,The myrtle
        and the oil tree;I will set in the desert the cypress tree and the pineAnd
        the box tree together,
      comments: []
    - name: '20: The Futility of Idols'
      title: The Futility of Idols
      number: 20
      content: That they may see and know,And consider and understand together,That
        the hand of the Lord has done this,And the Holy One of Israel has created
        it.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CPresent your case,\u201D says the Lord.\u201CBring forth your
        strong reasons,\u201D says the King of Jacob."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CLet them bring forth and show us what will happen;Let them
        show the former things, what they were,That we may consider them,And know
        the latter end of them;Or declare to us things to come."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Show the things that are to come hereafter,That we may know that you
        are gods;Yes, do good or do evil,That we may be dismayed and see it together.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: Indeed you are nothing,And your work is nothing;He  who chooses you
        is an abomination.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CI have raised up one from the north,And he shall come;From
        the rising of the sun he shall call on My name;And he shall come against
        princes as though mortar,As the potter treads clay."
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Who has declared from the beginning, that we may know?And former
        times, that we may say, \u2018He  is righteous\u2019?Surely there  is no
        one who shows,Surely there  is no one who declares,Surely there  is no one
        who hears your words."
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "The first time I  said to Zion,\u2018Look, there they are!\u2019And
        I will give to Jerusalem one who brings good tidings."
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: For I looked, and there  was no man;I looked among them, but there 
        was no counselor,Who, when I asked of them, could answer a word.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: Indeed they are all worthless;Their works are nothing;Their molded
        images are wind and confusion.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Servant of the Lord'
      title: The Servant of the Lord
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CBehold! My Servant whom I uphold,My Elect One in  whom My soul
        delights!I have put My Spirit upon Him;He will bring forth justice to the
        Gentiles."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: He will not cry out, nor raise His  voice,Nor cause His voice to be
        heard in the street.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: A bruised reed He will not break,And smoking flax He will not quench;He
        will bring forth justice for truth.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "He will not fail nor be discouraged,Till He has established justice
        in the earth;And the coastlands shall wait for His law.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Thus says God the Lord,Who created the heavens and stretched them
        out,Who spread forth the earth and that which comes from it,Who gives breath
        to the people on it,And spirit to those who walk on it:'
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CI, the Lord, have called You in righteousness,And will hold
        Your hand;I will keep You and give You as a covenant to the people,As a light
        to the Gentiles,"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: To open blind eyes,To bring out prisoners from the prison,Those who
        sit in darkness from the prison house.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: I am the Lord, that is My name;And My glory I will not give to another,Nor
        My praise to carved images.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Praise to the Lord'
      title: Praise to the Lord
      number: 9
      content: "Behold, the former things have come to pass,And new things I declare;Before
        they spring forth I tell you of them.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Sing to the Lord a new song,And His praise from the ends of the earth,You
        who go down to the sea, and all that is in it,You coastlands and you inhabitants
        of them!
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Let the wilderness and its cities lift up their  voice,The villages
        that Kedar inhabits.Let the inhabitants of Sela sing,Let them shout from
        the top of the mountains.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Let them give glory to the Lord,And declare His praise in the coastlands.
      comments: []
    - name: "13: Promise of the Lord\u2019s Help"
      title: "Promise of the Lord\u2019s Help"
      number: 13
      content: The Lord shall go forth like a mighty man;He shall stir up His zeal
        like a man of war.He shall cry out, yes, shout aloud;He shall prevail against
        His enemies.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CI have held My peace a long time,I have been still and restrained
        Myself.Now I will cry like a woman in labor,I will pant and gasp at once."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: I will lay waste the mountains and hills,And dry up all their vegetation;I
        will make the rivers coastlands,And I will dry up the pools.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: I will bring the blind by a way they did not know;I will lead them
        in paths they have not known.I will make darkness light before them,And crooked
        places straight.These things I will do for them,And not forsake them.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "They shall be turned back,They shall be greatly ashamed,Who trust
        in carved images,Who say to the molded images,\u2018You are our gods.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CHear, you deaf;And look, you blind, that you may see."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Who is blind but My servant,Or deaf as My messenger whom I send?Who
        is blind as he  who  is perfect,And blind as the Lord\u2019s servant?"
      comments: []
    - name: "20: Israel\u2019s Obstinate Disobedience"
      title: "Israel\u2019s Obstinate Disobedience"
      number: 20
      content: "Seeing many things, but you do not observe;Opening the ears, but
        he does not hear.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "The Lord is well pleased for His righteousness\u2019 sake;He will
        exalt the law and make it honorable."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But this is a people robbed and plundered;All of them are snared
        in holes,And they are hidden in prison houses;They are for prey, and no one
        delivers;For plunder, and no one says, \u201CRestore!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Who among you will give ear to this?Who will listen and hear for the
        time to come?
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: Who gave Jacob for plunder, and Israel to the robbers?Was it not the
        Lord,He against whom we have sinned?For they would not walk in His ways,Nor
        were they obedient to His law.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Therefore He has poured on him the fury of His angerAnd the strength
        of battle;It has set him on fire all around,Yet he did not know;And it burned
        him,Yet he did not take it to heart.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Redeemer of Israel'
      title: The Redeemer of Israel
      number: 1
      content: "But now, thus says the Lord, who created you, O Jacob,And He who
        formed you, O Israel:\u201CFear not, for I have redeemed you;I have called
        you by your name;You are Mine."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: When you pass through the waters, I will  be with you;And through
        the rivers, they shall not overflow you.When you walk through the fire, you
        shall not be burned,Nor shall the flame scorch you.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: For I am the Lord your God,The Holy One of Israel, your Savior;I gave
        Egypt for your ransom,Ethiopia and Seba in your place.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Since you were precious in My sight,You have been honored,And I have
        loved you;Therefore I will give men for you,And people for your life.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Fear not, for I am with you;I will bring your descendants from the
        east,And gather you from the west;
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "I will say to the north, \u2018Give them up!\u2019And to the south,
        \u2018Do not keep them back!\u2019Bring My sons from afar,And My daughters
        from the ends of the earth\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Everyone who is called by My name,Whom I have created for My glory;I
        have formed him, yes, I have made him.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Bring out the blind people who have eyes,And the deaf who have ears.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Let all the nations be gathered together,And let the people be assembled.Who
        among them can declare this,And show us former things?Let them bring out
        their witnesses, that they may be justified;Or let them hear and say, \u201CIt 
        is truth.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CYou  are My witnesses,\u201D says the Lord,\u201CAnd My servant
        whom I have chosen,That you may know and believe Me,And understand that I
        am He.Before Me there was no God formed,Nor shall there be after Me."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: I, even I, am the Lord,And besides Me there  is no savior.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "I have declared and saved,I have proclaimed,And there  was no foreign
        god among you;Therefore you are My witnesses,\u201DSays the Lord, \u201Cthat
        I am God."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Indeed before the day was, I am He;And there  is no one who can deliver
        out of My hand;I work, and who will reverse it?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Thus says the Lord, your Redeemer,The Holy One of Israel:\u201CFor
        your sake I will send to Babylon,And bring them all down as fugitives\u2014The
        Chaldeans, who rejoice in their ships."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "I am the Lord, your Holy One,The Creator of Israel, your King.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Thus says the Lord, who makes a way in the seaAnd a path through the
        mighty waters,
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Who brings forth the chariot and horse,The army and the power(They
        shall lie down together, they shall not rise;They are extinguished, they
        are quenched like a wick):'
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CDo not remember the former things,Nor consider the things of
        old."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Behold, I will do a new thing,Now it shall spring forth;Shall you
        not know it?I will even make a road in the wildernessAnd rivers in the desert.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: The beast of the field will honor Me,The jackals and the ostriches,Because
        I give waters in the wildernessAnd rivers in the desert,To give drink to
        My people, My chosen.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Pleading with Unfaithful Israel'
      title: Pleading with Unfaithful Israel
      number: 21
      content: This people I have formed for Myself;They shall declare My praise.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CBut you have not called upon Me, O Jacob;And you have been
        weary of Me, O Israel."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: You have not brought Me the sheep for your burnt offerings,Nor have
        you honored Me with your sacrifices.I have not caused you to serve with grain
        offerings,Nor wearied you with incense.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: You have bought Me no sweet cane with money,Nor have you satisfied
        Me with the fat of your sacrifices;But you have burdened Me with your sins,You
        have wearied Me with your iniquities.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CI, even I, am He who blots out your transgressions for My own
        sake;And I will not remember your sins."
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: Put Me in remembrance;Let us contend together;State your case, that
        you may be acquitted.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Your first father sinned,And your mediators have transgressed against
        Me.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: Therefore I will profane the princes of the sanctuary;I will give
        Jacob to the curse,And Israel to reproaches.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Blessing on Israel"
      title: "God\u2019s Blessing on Israel"
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CYet hear now, O Jacob My servant,And Israel whom I have chosen."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Thus says the Lord who made youAnd formed you from the womb, who
        will help you:\u2018Fear not, O Jacob My servant;And you, Jeshurun, whom
        I have chosen."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: For I will pour water on him who is thirsty,And floods on the dry
        ground;I will pour My Spirit on your descendants,And My blessing on your
        offspring;
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "They will spring up among the grassLike willows by the watercourses.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: There Is No Other God'
      title: There Is No Other God
      number: 5
      content: "One will say, \u2018I am the Lord\u2019s\u2019;Another will call
        himself by the name of Jacob;Another will write with his hand, \u2018The
        Lord\u2019s,\u2019And name himself by the name of Israel."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord, the King of Israel,And his Redeemer, the
        Lord of hosts:\u2018I am the First and I am the Last;Besides Me there  is
        no God."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: And who can proclaim as I do?Then let him declare it and set it in
        order for Me,Since I appointed the ancient people.And the things that are
        coming and shall come,Let them show these to them.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Idolatry Is Foolishness'
      title: Idolatry Is Foolishness
      number: 8
      content: "Do not fear, nor be afraid;Have I not told you from that time, and
        declared it?You are My witnesses.Is there a God besides Me?Indeed there 
        is no other Rock;I know not one.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Those who make an image, all of them are useless,And their precious
        things shall not profit;They are their own witnesses;They neither see nor
        know, that they may be ashamed.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Who would form a god or mold an imageThat profits him nothing?
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Surely all his companions would be ashamed;And the workmen, they are
        mere men.Let them all be gathered together,Let them stand up;Yet they shall
        fear,They shall be ashamed together.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: The blacksmith with the tongs works one in the coals,Fashions it with
        hammers,And works it with the strength of his arms.Even so, he is hungry,
        and his strength fails;He drinks no water and is faint.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: The craftsman stretches out his rule,He marks one out with chalk;He
        fashions it with a plane,He marks it out with the compass,And makes it like
        the figure of a man,According to the beauty of a man, that it may remain
        in the house.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: He cuts down cedars for himself,And takes the cypress and the oak;He
        secures it for himself among the trees of the forest.He plants a pine, and
        the rain nourishes it.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Then it shall be for a man to burn,For he will take some of it and
        warm himself;Yes, he kindles it and bakes bread;Indeed he makes a god and
        worships it;He makes it a carved image, and falls down to it.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "He burns half of it in the fire;With this half he eats meat;He roasts
        a roast, and is satisfied.He even warms himself and says,\u201CAh! I am warm,I
        have seen the fire.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And the rest of it he makes into a god,His carved image.He falls
        down before it and worships it,Prays to it and says,\u201CDeliver me, for
        you are my god!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: They do not know nor understand;For He has shut their eyes, so that
        they cannot see,And their hearts, so that they cannot understand.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And no one considers in his heart,Nor is  there knowledge nor understanding
        to say,\u201CI have burned half of it in the fire,Yes, I have also baked
        bread on its coals;I have roasted meat and eaten it;And shall I make the
        rest of it an abomination?Shall I fall down before a block of wood?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: Israel Is Not Forgotten'
      title: Israel Is Not Forgotten
      number: 20
      content: "He feeds on ashes;A deceived heart has turned him aside;And he cannot
        deliver his soul,Nor say, \u201CIs  there not a lie in my right hand?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CRemember these, O Jacob,And Israel, for you are My servant;I
        have formed you, you are My servant;O Israel, you will not be forgotten by
        Me!"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "I have blotted out, like a thick cloud, your transgressions,And like
        a cloud, your sins.Return to Me, for I have redeemed you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Judah Will Be Restored'
      title: Judah Will Be Restored
      number: 23
      content: Sing, O heavens, for the Lord has done it!Shout, you lower parts of
        the earth;Break forth into singing, you mountains,O forest, and every tree
        in it!For the Lord has redeemed Jacob,And glorified Himself in Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Thus says the Lord, your Redeemer,And He who formed you from the
        womb:\u201CI am the Lord, who makes all things,Who stretches out the heavens
        all alone,Who spreads abroad the earth by Myself;"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Who frustrates the signs of the babblers,And drives diviners mad;Who
        turns wise men backward,And makes their knowledge foolishness;
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Who confirms the word of His servant,And performs the counsel of
        His messengers;Who says to Jerusalem, \u2018You shall be inhabited,\u2019To
        the cities of Judah, \u2018You shall be built,\u2019And I will raise up her
        waste places;"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Who says to the deep, \u2018Be dry!And I will dry up your rivers\u2019;"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Who says of Cyrus, \u2018He  is My shepherd,And he shall perform
        all My pleasure,Saying to Jerusalem, \u201CYou shall be built,\u201DAnd to
        the temple, \u201CYour foundation shall be laid.\u201D \u2019"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Cyrus, God\u2019s Instrument"
      title: "Cyrus, God\u2019s Instrument"
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord to His anointed,To Cyrus, whose right hand
        I have held\u2014To subdue nations before himAnd loose the armor of kings,To
        open before him the double doors,So that the gates will not be shut:"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u2018I will go before youAnd make the crooked places straight;I
        will break in pieces the gates of bronzeAnd cut the bars of iron."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: I will give you the treasures of darknessAnd hidden riches of secret
        places,That you may know that I, the Lord,Who call you by your name,Am the
        God of Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For Jacob My servant\u2019s sake,And Israel My elect,I have even
        called you by your name;I have named you, though you have not known Me."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: I am the Lord, and there  is no other;There  is no God besides Me.I
        will gird you, though you have not known Me,
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: That they may know from the rising of the sun to its settingThat there 
        is none besides Me.I am the Lord, and there  is no other;
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "I form the light and create darkness,I make peace and create calamity;I,
        the Lord, do all these things.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CRain down, you heavens, from above,And let the skies pour down
        righteousness;Let the earth open, let them bring forth salvation,And let
        righteousness spring up together.I, the Lord, have created it."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CWoe to him who strives with his Maker!Let the potsherd strive
        with the potsherds of the earth!Shall the clay say to him who forms it, \u2018What
        are you making?\u2019Or shall your handiwork say, \u2018He has no hands\u2019?"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Woe to him who says to his father, \u2018What are you begetting?\u2019Or
        to the woman, \u2018What have you brought forth?\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Thus says the Lord,The Holy One of Israel, and his Maker:\u201CAsk
        Me of things to come concerning My sons;And concerning the work of My hands,
        you command Me."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "I have made the earth,And created man on it.I\u2014My hands\u2014stretched
        out the heavens,And all their host I have commanded."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: The Lord, the Only Savior'
      title: The Lord, the Only Savior
      number: 13
      content: "I have raised him up in righteousness,And I will direct all his ways;He
        shall build My cityAnd let My exiles go free,Not for price nor reward,\u201DSays
        the Lord of hosts."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Thus says the Lord:\u201CThe labor of Egypt and merchandise of CushAnd
        of the Sabeans, men of stature,Shall come over to you, and they shall be
        yours;They shall walk behind you,They shall come over in chains;And they
        shall bow down to you.They will make supplication to you, saying,  \u2018Surely
        God is in you,And there  is no other;There  is no other God.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Truly You are God, who hide Yourself,O God of Israel, the Savior!
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: They shall be ashamedAnd also disgraced, all of them;They shall go
        in confusion together,Who  are makers of idols.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: But Israel shall be saved by the LordWith an everlasting salvation;You
        shall not be ashamed or disgracedForever and ever.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "For thus says the Lord,Who created the heavens,Who is God,Who formed
        the earth and made it,Who has established it,Who did not create it in vain,Who
        formed it to be inhabited:\u201CI am the Lord, and there  is no other."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "I have not spoken in secret,In a dark place of the earth;I did not
        say to the seed of Jacob,\u2018Seek Me in vain\u2019;I, the Lord, speak righteousness,I
        declare things that are right."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CAssemble yourselves and come;Draw near together,You who  have
        escaped from the nations.They have no knowledge,Who carry the wood of their
        carved image,And pray to a god that cannot save."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Tell and bring forth your  case;Yes, let them take counsel together.Who
        has declared this from ancient time?Who has told it from that time?Have not
        I, the Lord?And there  is no other God besides Me,A just God and a Savior;There 
        is none besides Me.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CLook to Me, and be saved,All you ends of the earth!For I am
        God, and there  is no other."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: I have sworn by Myself;The word has gone out of My mouth in righteousness,And
        shall not return,That to Me every knee shall bow,Every tongue shall take
        an oath.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "He shall say,\u2018Surely in the Lord I have righteousness and strength.To
        Him men shall come,And all shall be ashamedWho are incensed against Him."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "In the Lord all the descendants of IsraelShall be justified, and
        shall glory.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Dead Idols and the Living God'
      title: Dead Idols and the Living God
      number: 1
      content: Bel bows down, Nebo stoops;Their idols were on the beasts and on the
        cattle.Your carriages were heavily loaded,A burden to the weary beast.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: They stoop, they bow down together;They could not deliver the burden,But
        have themselves gone into captivity.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CListen to Me, O house of Jacob,And all the remnant of the house
        of Israel,Who have been upheld by  Me from birth,Who have been carried from
        the womb:"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Even to your old age, I am He,And even to gray hairs I will carry
        you!I have made, and I will bear;Even I will carry, and will deliver you.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CTo whom will you liken Me, and make Me equalAnd compare Me,
        that we should be alike?"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: They lavish gold out of the bag,And weigh silver on the scales;They
        hire a goldsmith, and he makes it a god;They prostrate themselves, yes, they
        worship.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: They bear it on the shoulder, they carry itAnd set it in its place,
        and it stands;From its place it shall not move.Though one cries out to it,
        yet it cannot answerNor save him out of his trouble.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CRemember this, and show yourselves men;Recall to mind, O you
        transgressors."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Remember the former things of old,For I am God, and there  is no other;I 
        am God, and there  is none like Me,
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Declaring the end from the beginning,And from ancient times things
        that are not yet done,Saying, \u2018My counsel shall stand,And I will do
        all My pleasure,\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Calling a bird of prey from the east,The man who executes My counsel,
        from a far country.Indeed I have spoken it;I will also bring it to pass.I
        have purposed it;I will also do it.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CListen to Me, you stubborn-hearted,Who are far from righteousness:"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: I bring My righteousness near, it shall not be far off;My salvation
        shall not linger.And I will place salvation in Zion,For Israel My glory.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Humiliation of Babylon'
      title: The Humiliation of Babylon
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CCome down and sit in the dust,O virgin daughter of Babylon;Sit
        on the ground without a throne,O daughter of the Chaldeans!For you shall
        no more be calledTender and delicate."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Take the millstones and grind meal.Remove your veil,Take off the skirt,Uncover
        the thigh,Pass through the rivers.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Your nakedness shall be uncovered,Yes, your shame will be seen;I
        will take vengeance,And I will not arbitrate with a man.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: As  for  our Redeemer, the Lord of hosts is His name,The Holy One
        of Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CSit in silence, and go into darkness,O daughter of the Chaldeans;For
        you shall no longer be calledThe Lady of Kingdoms."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: I was angry with My people;I have profaned My inheritance,And given
        them into your hand.You showed them no mercy;On the elderly you laid your
        yoke very heavily.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And you said, \u2018I shall be a lady forever,\u2019So that you did
        not take these things to heart,Nor remember the latter end of them."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CTherefore hear this now, you  who  are given to pleasures,Who
        dwell securely,Who say in your heart, \u2018I am, and there  is no one else
        besides me;I shall not sit as a widow,Nor shall I know the loss of children\u2019;"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: But these two things shall come to youIn a moment, in one day:The
        loss of children, and widowhood.They shall come upon you in their fullnessBecause
        of the multitude of your sorceries,For the great abundance of your enchantments.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CFor you have trusted in your wickedness;You have said, \u2018No
        one sees me\u2019;Your wisdom and your knowledge have warped you;And you
        have said in your heart,\u2018I am, and there  is no one else besides me.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Therefore evil shall come upon you;You shall not know from where it
        arises.And trouble shall fall upon you;You will not be able to put it off.And
        desolation shall come upon you suddenly,Which you shall not know.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CStand now with your enchantmentsAnd the multitude of your sorceries,In
        which you have labored from your youth\u2014Perhaps you will be able to profit,Perhaps
        you will prevail."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: You are wearied in the multitude of your counsels;Let now the astrologers,
        the stargazers,And the monthly prognosticatorsStand up and save youFrom what
        shall come upon you.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Behold, they shall be as stubble,The fire shall burn them;They shall
        not deliver themselvesFrom the power of the flame;It  shall not be a coal
        to be warmed by,Nor a fire to sit before!
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Thus shall they be to youWith whom you have labored,Your merchants
        from your youth;They shall wander each one to his quarter.No one shall save
        you.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Israel Refined for God\u2019s Glory"
      title: "Israel Refined for God\u2019s Glory"
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CHear this, O house of Jacob,Who are called by the name of Israel,And
        have come forth from the wellsprings of Judah;Who swear by the name of the
        Lord,And make mention of the God of Israel,But  not in truth or in righteousness;"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For they call themselves after the holy city,And lean on the God
        of Israel;The Lord of hosts is His name:'
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CI have declared the former things from the beginning;They went
        forth from My mouth, and I caused them to hear it.Suddenly I did them,  and
        they came to pass."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Because I knew that you were obstinate,And your neck was an iron sinew,And
        your brow bronze,
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Even from the beginning I have declared it to you;Before it came
        to pass I proclaimed it to you,Lest you should say, \u2018My idol has done
        them,And my carved image and my molded imageHave commanded them.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CYou have heard;See all this.And will you not declare it?I have
        made you hear new things from this time,Even hidden things, and you did not
        know them."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "They are created now and not from the beginning;And before this day
        you have not heard them,Lest you should say, \u2018Of course I knew them.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Surely you did not hear,Surely you did not know;Surely from long ago
        your ear was not opened.For I knew that you would deal very treacherously,And
        were called a transgressor from the womb.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CFor My name\u2019s sake I will defer My anger,And for My praise
        I will restrain it from you,So that I do not cut you off."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Behold, I have refined you, but not as silver;I have tested you in
        the furnace of affliction.
      comments: []
    - name: "11: God\u2019s Ancient Plan to Redeem Israel"
      title: "God\u2019s Ancient Plan to Redeem Israel"
      number: 11
      content: For My own sake, for My own sake, I will do it;For how should My 
        name be profaned?And I will not give My glory to another.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CListen to Me, O Jacob,And Israel, My called:I am He, I am the
        First,I am also the Last."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Indeed My hand has laid the foundation of the earth,And My right hand
        has stretched out the heavens;When  I call to them,They stand up together.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CAll of you, assemble yourselves, and hear!Who among them has
        declared these things?The Lord loves him;He shall do His pleasure on Babylon,And
        His arm shall  be  against the Chaldeans."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: I, even I, have spoken;Yes, I have called him,I have brought him,
        and his way will prosper.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CCome near to Me, hear this:I have not spoken in secret from
        the beginning;From the time that it was, I was there.And now the Lord God
        and His SpiritHave sent Me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Thus says the Lord, your Redeemer,The Holy One of Israel:\u201CI
        am the Lord your God,Who teaches you to profit,Who leads you by the way you
        should go."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Oh, that you had heeded My commandments!Then your peace would have
        been like a river,And your righteousness like the waves of the sea.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Your descendants also would have been like the sand,And the offspring
        of your body like the grains of sand;His name would not have been cut offNor
        destroyed from before Me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Go forth from Babylon!Flee from the Chaldeans!With a voice of singing,Declare,
        proclaim this,Utter it to the end of the earth;Say, \u201CThe Lord has redeemedHis
        servant Jacob!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: And they did not thirstWhen He led them through the deserts;He caused
        the waters to flow from the rock for them;He also split the rock, and the
        waters gushed out.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CThere is no peace,\u201D says the Lord, \u201Cfor the wicked.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Servant, the Light to the Gentiles'
      title: The Servant, the Light to the Gentiles
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CListen, O coastlands, to Me,And take heed, you peoples from
        afar!The Lord has called Me from the womb;From the matrix of My mother He
        has made mention of My name."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And He has made My mouth like a sharp sword;In the shadow of His
        hand He has hidden Me,And made Me a polished shaft;In His quiver He has hidden
        Me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CAnd He said to me,\u2018You are My servant, O Israel,In whom
        I will be glorified.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then I said, \u2018I have labored in vain,I have spent my strength
        for nothing and in vain;Yet surely my just reward is with the Lord,And my
        work with my God.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CAnd now the Lord says,Who formed Me from the womb to  be His
        Servant,To bring Jacob back to Him,So that Israel is gathered to Him(For
        I shall be glorious in the eyes of the Lord,And My God shall be My strength),"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Indeed He says,\u2018It is too small a thing that You should be My
        ServantTo raise up the tribes of Jacob,And to restore the preserved ones
        of Israel;I will also give You as a light to the Gentiles,That You should
        be My salvation to the ends of the earth.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Thus says the Lord,The Redeemer of Israel, their Holy One,To Him
        whom man despises,To Him whom the nation abhors,To the Servant of rulers:\u201CKings
        shall see and arise,Princes also shall worship,Because of the Lord who is
        faithful,The Holy One of Israel;And He has chosen You.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Thus says the Lord:\u201CIn an acceptable time I have heard You,And
        in the day of salvation I have helped You;I will preserve You and give YouAs
        a covenant to the people,To restore the earth,To cause them to inherit the
        desolate heritages;"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "That You may say to the prisoners, \u2018Go forth,\u2019To those
        who are in darkness, \u2018Show yourselves.\u2019\u201CThey shall feed along
        the roads,And their pastures shall  be on all desolate heights."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: They shall neither hunger nor thirst,Neither heat nor sun shall strike
        them;For He who has mercy on them will lead them,Even by the springs of water
        He will guide them.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: I will make each of My mountains a road,And My highways shall be elevated.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Surely these shall come from afar;Look! Those from the north and
        the west,And these from the land of Sinim.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: God Will Remember Zion'
      title: God Will Remember Zion
      number: 13
      content: Sing, O heavens!Be joyful, O earth!And break out in singing, O mountains!For
        the Lord has comforted His people,And will have mercy on His afflicted.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But Zion said, \u201CThe Lord has forsaken me,And my Lord has forgotten
        me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CCan a woman forget her nursing child,And not have compassion
        on the son of her womb?Surely they may forget,Yet I will not forget you."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: See, I have inscribed you on the palms of  My  hands;Your walls are
        continually before Me.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Your sons shall make haste;Your destroyers and those who laid you
        wasteShall go away from you.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Lift up your eyes, look around and see;All these gather together
        and come to you.As I live,\u201D says the Lord,\u201CYou shall surely clothe
        yourselves with them all as an ornament,And bind them on  you as a bride
        does."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CFor your waste and desolate places,And the land of your destruction,Will
        even now be too small for the inhabitants;And those who swallowed you up
        will be far away."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "The children you will have,After you have lost the others,Will say
        again in your ears,\u2018The place is too small for me;Give me a place where
        I may dwell.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then you will say in your heart,\u2018Who has begotten these for
        me,Since I have lost my children and am desolate,A captive, and wandering
        to and fro?And who has brought these up?There I was, left alone;But these,
        where were they?\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Thus says the Lord God:\u201CBehold, I will lift My hand in an oath
        to the nations,And set up My standard for the peoples;They shall bring your
        sons in their arms,And your daughters shall be carried on their shoulders;"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Kings shall be your foster fathers,And their queens your nursing
        mothers;They shall bow down to you with their faces to the earth,And lick
        up the dust of your feet.Then you will know that I am the Lord,For they shall
        not be ashamed who wait for Me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: Shall the prey be taken from the mighty,Or the captives of the righteous
        be delivered?
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "But thus says the Lord:\u201CEven the captives of the mighty shall
        be taken away,And the prey of the terrible be delivered;For I will contend
        with him who contends with you,And I will save your children."
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "I will feed those who oppress you with their own flesh,And they shall
        be drunk with their own blood as with sweet wine.All flesh shall knowThat
        I, the Lord, am your Savior,And your Redeemer, the Mighty One of Jacob.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The Servant, Israel\u2019s Hope"
      title: "The Servant, Israel\u2019s Hope"
      number: 1
      content: "Thus says the Lord:\u201CWhere is  the certificate of your mother\u2019s
        divorce,Whom I have put away?Or which of My creditors is  it to whom I have
        sold you?For your iniquities you have sold yourselves,And for your transgressions
        your mother has been put away."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Why, when I came, was  there no man?Why, when I called, was  there
        none to answer?Is My hand shortened at all that it cannot redeem?Or have
        I no power to deliver?Indeed with My rebuke I dry up the sea,I make the rivers
        a wilderness;Their fish stink because there  is no water,And die of thirst.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "I clothe the heavens with blackness,And I make sackcloth their covering.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CThe Lord God has given MeThe tongue of the learned,That I should
        know how to speakA word in season to him  who  is  weary.He awakens Me morning
        by morning,He awakens My earTo hear as the learned."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: The Lord God  has opened My ear;And I was not rebellious,Nor did I
        turn away.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: I gave My back to those who struck Me,And My cheeks to those who plucked
        out the beard;I did not hide My face from shame and spitting.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CFor the Lord God will help Me;Therefore I will not be disgraced;Therefore
        I have set My face like a flint,And I know that I will not be ashamed."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: He  is near who justifies Me;Who will contend with Me?Let us stand
        together.Who is My adversary?Let him come near Me.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Surely the Lord God will help Me;Who is he who will condemn Me?Indeed
        they will all grow old like a garment;The moth will eat them up.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CWho among you fears the Lord?Who obeys the voice of His Servant?Who
        walks in darknessAnd has no light?Let him trust in the name of the LordAnd
        rely upon his God."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Look, all you who kindle a fire,Who encircle yourselves with sparks:Walk
        in the light of your fire and in the sparks you have kindled\u2014This you
        shall have from My hand:You shall lie down in torment."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Lord Comforts Zion'
      title: The Lord Comforts Zion
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CListen to Me, you who follow after righteousness,You who seek
        the Lord:Look to the rock from  which you were hewn,And to the hole of the
        pit from  which you were dug."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Look to Abraham your father,And to Sarah who bore you;For I called
        him alone,And blessed him and increased him.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: For the Lord will comfort Zion,He will comfort all her waste places;He
        will make her wilderness like Eden,And her desert like the garden of the
        Lord;Joy and gladness will be found in it,Thanksgiving and the voice of melody.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CListen to Me, My people;And give ear to Me, O My nation:For
        law will proceed from Me,And I will make My justice restAs a light of the
        peoples."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: My righteousness is near,My salvation has gone forth,And My arms will
        judge the peoples;The coastlands will wait upon Me,And on My arm they will
        trust.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Lift up your eyes to the heavens,And look on the earth beneath.For
        the heavens will vanish away like smoke,The earth will grow old like a garment,And
        those who dwell in it will die in like manner;But My salvation will be forever,And
        My righteousness will not be abolished.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CListen to Me, you who know righteousness,You people in whose
        heart is My law:Do not fear the reproach of men,Nor be afraid of their insults."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "For the moth will eat them up like a garment,And the worm will eat
        them like wool;But My righteousness will be forever,And My salvation from
        generation to generation.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Awake, awake, put on strength,O arm of the Lord!Awake as in the ancient
        days,In the generations of old.Are You not the  arm that cut Rahab apart,And
        wounded the serpent?
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Are You not the  One who dried up the sea,The waters of the great
        deep;That made the depths of the sea a roadFor the redeemed to cross over?
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: So the ransomed of the Lord shall return,And come to Zion with singing,With
        everlasting joy on their heads.They shall obtain joy and gladness;Sorrow
        and sighing shall flee away.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CI, even I, am He who comforts you.Who are you that you should
        be afraidOf a man who will die,And of the son of a man who will be made like
        grass?"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: And you forget the Lord your Maker,Who stretched out the heavensAnd
        laid the foundations of the earth;You have feared continually every dayBecause
        of the fury of the oppressor,When he  has prepared to destroy.And where is
        the fury of the oppressor?
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: The captive exile hastens, that he may be loosed,That he should not
        die in the pit,And that his bread should not fail.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But I am the Lord your God,Who divided the sea whose waves roared\u2014The
        Lord of hosts is His name."
      comments: []
    - name: "16: God\u2019s Fury Removed"
      title: "God\u2019s Fury Removed"
      number: 16
      content: "And I have put My words in your mouth;I have covered you with the
        shadow of My hand,That I may plant the heavens,Lay the foundations of the
        earth,And say to Zion, \u2018You are My people.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Awake, awake!Stand up, O Jerusalem,You who have drunk at the hand
        of the LordThe cup of His fury;You have drunk the dregs of the cup of trembling,And
        drained it out.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: There  is no one to guide herAmong all the sons she has brought forth;Nor
        is  there  any who takes her by the handAmong all the sons she has brought
        up.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "These two things have come to you;Who will be sorry for you?\u2014Desolation
        and destruction, famine and sword\u2014By whom will I comfort you?"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Your sons have fainted,They lie at the head of all the streets,Like
        an antelope in a net;They are full of the fury of the Lord,The rebuke of
        your God.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Therefore please hear this, you afflicted,And drunk but not with wine.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Thus says your Lord,The Lord and your God,Who  pleads the cause of
        His people:\u201CSee, I have taken out of your handThe cup of trembling,The
        dregs of the cup of My fury;You shall no longer drink it."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "But I will put it into the hand of those who afflict you,Who have
        said to you,\u2018Lie down, that we may walk over you.\u2019And you have
        laid your body like the ground,And as the street, for those who walk over.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: God Redeems Jerusalem'
      title: God Redeems Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: Awake, awake!Put on your strength, O Zion;Put on your beautiful garments,O
        Jerusalem, the holy city!For the uncircumcised and the uncleanShall no longer
        come to you.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Shake yourself from the dust, arise;Sit down, O Jerusalem!Loose yourself
        from the bonds of your neck,O captive daughter of Zion!
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For thus says the Lord:\u201CYou have sold yourselves for nothing,And
        you shall be redeemed without money.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For thus says the Lord God:\u201CMy people went down at firstInto
        Egypt to dwell there;Then the Assyrian oppressed them without cause."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Now therefore, what have I here,\u201D says the Lord,\u201CThat My
        people are taken away for nothing?Those who rule over themMake them wail,\u201D
        says the Lord,\u201CAnd My name is  blasphemed continually every day."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Therefore My people shall know My name;Therefore they  shall  know
        in that dayThat I am He who speaks:\u2018Behold, it  is I.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "How beautiful upon the mountainsAre the feet of him who brings good
        news,Who proclaims peace,Who brings glad tidings of good things,Who proclaims
        salvation,Who says to Zion,\u201CYour God reigns!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Your watchmen shall lift up their voices,With their voices they shall
        sing together;For they shall see eye to eyeWhen the Lord brings back Zion.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Break forth into joy, sing together,You waste places of Jerusalem!For
        the Lord has comforted His people,He has redeemed Jerusalem.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: The Lord has made bare His holy armIn the eyes of all the nations;And
        all the ends of the earth shall seeThe salvation of our God.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Depart! Depart! Go out from there,Touch no unclean thing;Go out from
        the midst of her,Be clean,You who bear the vessels of the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: The Sin-Bearing Servant'
      title: The Sin-Bearing Servant
      number: 12
      content: For you shall not go out with haste,Nor go by flight;For the Lord
        will go before you,And the God of Israel will  be your rear guard.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Behold, My Servant shall deal prudently;He shall be exalted and extolled
        and be very high.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Just as many were astonished at you,So His visage was marred more
        than any man,And His form more than the sons of men;
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: So shall He sprinkle many nations.Kings shall shut their mouths at
        Him;For what had not been told them they shall see,And what they had not
        heard they shall consider.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: Who has believed our report?And to whom has the arm of the Lord been
        revealed?
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: For He shall grow up before Him as a tender plant,And as a root out
        of dry ground.He has no form or comeliness;And when we see Him,There  is
        no beauty that we should desire Him.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: He is despised and rejected by men,A Man of sorrows and acquainted
        with grief.And we hid, as it were, our faces from Him;He was despised, and
        we did not esteem Him.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Surely He has borne our griefsAnd carried our sorrows;Yet we esteemed
        Him stricken,Smitten by God, and afflicted.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: But He was  wounded for our transgressions,He  was bruised for our
        iniquities;The chastisement for our peace was upon Him,And by His stripes
        we are healed.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: All we like sheep have gone astray;We have turned, every one, to his
        own way;And the Lord has laid on Him the iniquity of us all.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: He was oppressed and He was afflicted,Yet He opened not His mouth;He
        was led as a lamb to the slaughter,And as a sheep before its shearers is
        silent,So He opened not His mouth.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: He was taken from prison and from judgment,And who will declare His
        generation?For He was cut off from the land of the living;For the transgressions
        of My people He was stricken.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And they made His grave with the wicked\u2014But with the rich at
        His death,Because He had done no violence,Nor was  any  deceit in His mouth."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Yet it pleased the Lord to bruise Him;He has put Him to grief.When
        You make His soul an offering for sin,He shall see His seed, He shall prolong
        His days,And the pleasure of the Lord shall prosper in His hand.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: He shall see the labor of His soul, and be satisfied.By His knowledge
        My righteous Servant shall justify many,For He shall bear their iniquities.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Therefore I will divide Him a portion with the great,And He shall
        divide the spoil with the strong,Because He poured out His soul unto death,And
        He was numbered with the transgressors,And He bore the sin of many,And made
        intercession for the transgressors.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Perpetual Covenant of Peace'
      title: A Perpetual Covenant of Peace
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CSing, O barren,You who have not borne!Break forth into singing,
        and cry aloud,You who have not labored with child!For more are the children
        of the desolateThan the children of the married woman,\u201D says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CEnlarge the place of your tent,And let them stretch out the
        curtains of your dwellings;Do not spare;Lengthen your cords,And strengthen
        your stakes."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: For you shall expand to the right and to the left,And your descendants
        will inherit the nations,And make the desolate cities inhabited.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CDo not fear, for you will not be ashamed;Neither be disgraced,
        for you will not be put to shame;For you will forget the shame of your youth,And
        will not remember the reproach of your widowhood anymore."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: For your Maker is your husband,The Lord of hosts is His name;And your
        Redeemer is the Holy One of Israel;He is called the God of the whole earth.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For the Lord  has called youLike a woman forsaken and grieved in
        spirit,Like a youthful wife when you were refused,\u201DSays your God."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CFor a mere moment I have forsaken you,But with great mercies
        I will gather you."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "With a little wrath I hid My face from you for a moment;But with
        everlasting kindness I will have mercy on you,\u201DSays the Lord, your Redeemer."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CFor this is like the waters of Noah to Me;For as I have swornThat
        the waters of Noah would no longer cover the earth,So have I swornThat I
        would not be angry with you, nor rebuke you."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "For the mountains shall departAnd the hills be removed,But My kindness
        shall not depart from you,Nor shall My covenant of peace be removed,\u201DSays
        the Lord, who has mercy on you."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CO you afflicted one,Tossed with tempest, and not comforted,Behold,
        I will lay your stones with colorful gems,And lay your foundations with sapphires."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: I will make your pinnacles of rubies,Your gates of crystal,And all
        your walls of precious stones.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: All your children shall  be  taught by the Lord,And great shall  be
        the peace of your children.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: In righteousness you shall be established;You shall be far from oppression,
        for you shall not fear;And from terror, for it shall not come near you.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Indeed they shall surely assemble, but not because of Me.Whoever assembles
        against you shall fall for your sake.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CBehold, I have created the blacksmithWho blows the coals in
        the fire,Who brings forth an instrument for his work;And I have created the
        spoiler to destroy."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "No weapon formed against you shall prosper,And every tongue which
        rises against you in judgmentYou shall condemn.This is the heritage of the
        servants of the Lord,And their righteousness is from Me,\u201DSays the Lord."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: An Invitation to Abundant Life'
      title: An Invitation to Abundant Life
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CHo! Everyone who thirsts,Come to the waters;And you who have
        no money,Come, buy and eat.Yes, come, buy wine and milkWithout money and
        without price."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Why do you spend money for what  is not bread,And your wages for what
        does not satisfy?Listen carefully to Me, and eat what  is good,And let your
        soul delight itself in abundance.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Incline your ear, and come to Me.Hear, and your soul shall live;And
        I will make an everlasting covenant with you\u2014The sure mercies of David."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Indeed I have given him as  a witness to the people,A leader and commander
        for the people.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Surely you shall call a nation you do not know,And nations who do
        not know you shall run to you,Because of the Lord your God,And the Holy One
        of Israel;For He has glorified you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Seek the Lord while He may be found,Call upon Him while He is near.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Let the wicked forsake his way,And the unrighteous man his thoughts;Let
        him return to the Lord,And He will have mercy on him;And to our God,For He
        will abundantly pardon.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CFor My thoughts are not your thoughts,Nor are your ways My
        ways,\u201D says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CFor  as the heavens are higher than the earth,So are My ways
        higher than your ways,And My thoughts than your thoughts."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CFor as the rain comes down, and the snow from heaven,And do
        not return there,But water the earth,And make it bring forth and bud,That
        it may give seed to the sowerAnd bread to the eater,"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: So shall My word be that goes forth from My mouth;It shall not return
        to Me void,But it shall accomplish what I please,And it shall prosper in 
        the  thing for which I sent it.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CFor you shall go out with joy,And be led out with peace;The
        mountains and the hillsShall break forth into singing before you,And all
        the trees of the field shall clap their hands."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Instead of the thorn shall come up the cypress tree,And instead of
        the brier shall come up the myrtle tree;And it shall be to the Lord  for
        a name,For an everlasting sign that shall not be cut off.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Salvation for the Gentiles'
      title: Salvation for the Gentiles
      number: 1
      content: "Thus says the Lord:\u201CKeep justice, and do righteousness,For My
        salvation is about to come,And My righteousness to be revealed."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Blessed is the man who does this,And the son of man who lays hold
        on it;Who keeps from defiling the Sabbath,And keeps his hand from doing any
        evil.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Do not let the son of the foreignerWho has joined himself to the
        LordSpeak, saying,\u201CThe Lord has utterly separated me from His people\u201D;Nor
        let the eunuch say,\u201CHere I am, a dry tree.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For thus says the Lord:\u201CTo the eunuchs who keep My Sabbaths,And
        choose what pleases Me,And hold fast My covenant,"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Even to them I will give in My houseAnd within My walls a place and
        a nameBetter than that of sons and daughters;I will give them an everlasting
        nameThat shall not be cut off.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CAlso the sons of the foreignerWho join themselves to the Lord,
        to serve Him,And to love the name of the Lord, to be His servants\u2014Everyone
        who keeps from defiling the Sabbath,And holds fast My covenant\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Even them I will bring to My holy mountain,And make them joyful in
        My house of prayer.Their burnt offerings and their sacrificesWill  be  accepted
        on My altar;For My house shall be called a house of prayer for all nations.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: "8: Israel\u2019s Irresponsible Leaders"
      title: "Israel\u2019s Irresponsible Leaders"
      number: 8
      content: "The Lord God, who gathers the outcasts of Israel, says,\u201CYet
        I will gather to himOthers besides those who are gathered to him.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: All you beasts of the field, come to devour,All you beasts in the
        forest.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: His watchmen are  blind,They are all ignorant;They are all dumb dogs,They
        cannot bark;Sleeping, lying down, loving to slumber.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Yes, they  are  greedy dogsWhich  never have enough.And they are shepherdsWho
        cannot understand;They all look to their own way,Every one for his own gain,From
        his own territory.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CCome,\u201D one  says, \u201CI will bring wine,And we will
        fill ourselves with intoxicating drink;Tomorrow will be as today,And much
        more abundant.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Israel\u2019s Futile Idolatry"
      title: "Israel\u2019s Futile Idolatry"
      number: 1
      content: The righteous perishes,And no man takes it to heart;Merciful men are
        taken away,While no one considersThat the righteous is taken away from evil.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: He shall enter into peace;They shall rest in their beds,Each  one
        walking in his uprightness.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CBut come here,You sons of the sorceress,You offspring of the
        adulterer and the harlot!"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Whom do you ridicule?Against whom do you make a wide mouthAnd stick
        out the tongue?Are you not children of transgression,Offspring of falsehood,
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Inflaming yourselves with gods under every green tree,Slaying the
        children in the valleys,Under the clefts of the rocks?
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Among the smooth stones of the streamIs your portion;They, they, are
        your lot!Even to them you have poured a drink offering,You have offered a
        grain offering.Should I receive comfort in these?
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201COn a lofty and high mountainYou have set your bed;Even there
        you went upTo offer sacrifice."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Also behind the doors and their postsYou have set up your remembrance;For
        you have uncovered yourself to  those  other than Me,And have gone up to
        them;You have enlarged your bedAnd made a  covenant with them;You have loved
        their bed,Where you saw their nudity.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: You went to the king with ointment,And increased your perfumes;You
        sent your messengers far off,And even descended to Sheol.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "You are wearied in the length of your way;Yet you did not say, \u2018There
        is no hope.\u2019You have found the life of your hand;Therefore you were
        not grieved."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CAnd of whom have you been afraid, or feared,That you have liedAnd
        not remembered Me,Nor taken it to your heart?Is it not because I have held
        My peace from of oldThat you do not fear Me?"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: I will declare your righteousnessAnd your works,For they will not
        profit you.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Healing for the Backslider'
      title: Healing for the Backslider
      number: 13
      content: "When you cry out,Let your collection of  idols deliver you.But the
        wind will carry them all away,A breath will take them.But he who puts his
        trust in Me shall possess the land,And shall inherit My holy mountain.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And one shall say,\u201CHeap it up! Heap it up!Prepare the way,Take
        the stumbling block out of the way of My people.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "For thus says the High and Lofty OneWho inhabits eternity, whose
        name is Holy:\u201CI dwell in the high and holy place,With him who has a
        contrite and humble spirit,To revive the spirit of the humble,And to revive
        the heart of the contrite ones."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: For I will not contend forever,Nor will I always be angry;For the
        spirit would fail before Me,And the souls which I have made.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: For the iniquity of his covetousnessI was angry and struck him;I hid
        and was angry,And he went on backsliding in the way of his heart.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: I have seen his ways, and will heal him;I will also lead him,And restore
        comforts to himAnd to his mourners.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CI create the fruit of the lips:Peace, peace to him  who  is
        far off and to him  who  is near,\u201DSays the Lord,\u201CAnd I will heal
        him.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: But the wicked are like the troubled sea,When it cannot rest,Whose
        waters cast up mire and dirt.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CThere is no peace,\u201DSays my God, \u201Cfor the wicked.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Fasting that Pleases God'
      title: Fasting that Pleases God
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CCry aloud, spare not;Lift up your voice like a trumpet;Tell
        My people their transgression,And the house of Jacob their sins."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Yet they seek Me daily,And delight to know My ways,As a nation that
        did righteousness,And did not forsake the ordinance of their God.They ask
        of Me the ordinances of justice;They take delight in approaching God.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u2018Why have we fasted,\u2019 they  say, \u2018and You have not
        seen?Why have we afflicted our souls, and You take no notice?\u2019\u201CIn
        fact, in the day of your fast you find pleasure,And exploit all your laborers."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Indeed you fast for strife and debate,And to strike with the fist
        of wickedness.You will not fast as you  do this day,To make your voice heard
        on high.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Is it a fast that I have chosen,A day for a man to afflict his soul?Is 
        it to bow down his head like a bulrush,And to spread out sackcloth and ashes?Would
        you call this a fast,And an acceptable day to the Lord?
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CIs this not the fast that I have chosen:To loose the bonds
        of wickedness,To undo the heavy burdens,To let the oppressed go free,And
        that you break every yoke?"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Is  it not to share your bread with the hungry,And that you bring
        to your house the poor who are cast out;When you see the naked, that you
        cover him,And not hide yourself from your own flesh?
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Then your light shall break forth like the morning,Your healing shall
        spring forth speedily,And your righteousness shall go before you;The glory
        of the Lord shall be your rear guard.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then you shall call, and the Lord will answer;You shall cry, and
        He will say, \u2018Here I am.\u2019\u201CIf you take away the yoke from your
        midst,The pointing of the finger, and speaking wickedness,"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: If you extend your soul to the hungryAnd satisfy the afflicted soul,Then
        your light shall dawn in the darkness,And your darkness shall be as the noonday.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: The Lord will guide you continually,And satisfy your soul in drought,And
        strengthen your bones;You shall be like a watered garden,And like a spring
        of water, whose waters do not fail.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Those from among youShall build the old waste places;You shall raise
        up the foundations of many generations;And you shall be called the Repairer
        of the Breach,The Restorer of Streets to Dwell In.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CIf you turn away your foot from the Sabbath,From doing your
        pleasure on My holy day,And call the Sabbath a delight,The holy day of the
        Lord honorable,And shall honor Him, not doing your own ways,Nor finding your
        own pleasure,Nor speaking your  own words,"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then you shall delight yourself in the Lord;And I will cause you
        to ride on the high hills of the earth,And feed you with the heritage of
        Jacob your father.The mouth of the Lord has spoken.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Separated from God'
      title: Separated from God
      number: 1
      content: "Behold, the Lord\u2019s hand is not shortened,That it cannot save;Nor
        His ear heavy,That it cannot hear."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: But your iniquities have separated you from your God;And your sins
        have hidden His face from you,So that He will not hear.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: For your hands are defiled with blood,And your fingers with iniquity;Your
        lips have spoken lies,Your tongue has muttered perversity.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: No one calls for justice,Nor does any plead for truth.They trust in
        empty words and speak lies;They conceive evil and bring forth iniquity.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "They hatch vipers\u2019 eggs and weave the spider\u2019s web;He who
        eats of their eggs dies,And from that which is crushed a viper breaks out."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Their webs will not become garments,Nor will they cover themselves
        with their works;Their works are works of iniquity,And the act of violence
        is in their hands.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Their feet run to evil,And they make haste to shed innocent blood;Their
        thoughts are thoughts of iniquity;Wasting and destruction are in their paths.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Sin Confessed'
      title: Sin Confessed
      number: 8
      content: The way of peace they have not known,And there  is no justice in their
        ways;They have made themselves crooked paths;Whoever takes that way shall
        not know peace.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Therefore justice is far from us,Nor does righteousness overtake us;We
        look for light, but there is darkness!For brightness, but we walk in blackness!
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: We grope for the wall like the blind,And we grope as if we  had no
        eyes;We stumble at noonday as at twilight;We  are as dead men in desolate
        places.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: We all growl like bears,And moan sadly like doves;We look for justice,
        but there  is none;For salvation, but it is far from us.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For our transgressions are multiplied before You,And our sins testify
        against us;For our transgressions are with us,And as  for our iniquities,
        we know them:'
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: In transgressing and lying against the Lord,And departing from our
        God,Speaking oppression and revolt,Conceiving and uttering from the heart
        words of falsehood.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Justice is turned back,And righteousness stands afar off;For truth
        is fallen in the street,And equity cannot enter.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: The Redeemer of Zion'
      title: The Redeemer of Zion
      number: 15
      content: So truth fails,And he who departs from evil makes himself a prey.Then
        the Lord saw it, and it displeased HimThat there  was no justice.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: He saw that there  was no man,And wondered that there  was no intercessor;Therefore
        His own arm brought salvation for Him;And His own righteousness, it sustained
        Him.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: For He put on righteousness as a breastplate,And a helmet of salvation
        on His head;He put on the garments of vengeance for clothing,And was clad
        with zeal as a cloak.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: According to their deeds, accordingly He will repay,Fury to His adversaries,Recompense
        to His enemies;The coastlands He will fully repay.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: So shall they fearThe name of the Lord from the west,And His glory
        from the rising of the sun;When the enemy comes in like a flood,The Spirit
        of the Lord will lift up a standard against him.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CThe Redeemer will come to Zion,And to those who turn from transgression
        in Jacob,\u201DSays the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CAs for Me,\u201D says the Lord, \u201Cthis is My covenant with
        them: My Spirit who is upon you, and My words which I have put in your mouth,
        shall not depart from your mouth, nor from the mouth of your descendants,
        nor from the mouth of your descendants\u2019 descendants,\u201D says the
        Lord, \u201Cfrom this time and forevermore.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Gentiles Bless Zion'
      title: The Gentiles Bless Zion
      number: 1
      content: Arise, shine;For your light has come!And the glory of the Lord is
        risen upon you.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: For behold, the darkness shall cover the earth,And deep darkness the
        people;But the Lord will arise over you,And His glory will be seen upon you.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: The Gentiles shall come to your light,And kings to the brightness
        of your rising.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CLift up your eyes all around, and see:They all gather together,
        they come to you;Your sons shall come from afar,And your daughters shall
        be nursed at your side."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Then you shall see and become radiant,And your heart shall swell with
        joy;Because the abundance of the sea shall be turned to you,The wealth of
        the Gentiles shall come to you.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: The multitude of camels shall cover your land,The dromedaries of Midian
        and Ephah;All those from Sheba shall come;They shall bring gold and incense,And
        they shall proclaim the praises of the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: All the flocks of Kedar shall be gathered together to you,The rams
        of Nebaioth shall minister to you;They shall ascend with acceptance on My
        altar,And I will glorify the house of My glory.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CWho are these who fly like a cloud,And like doves to their
        roosts?"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Surely the coastlands shall wait for Me;And the ships of Tarshish
        will  come first,To bring your sons from afar,Their silver and their gold
        with them,To the name of the Lord your God,And to the Holy One of Israel,Because
        He has glorified you.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CThe sons of foreigners shall build up your walls,And their
        kings shall minister to you;For in My wrath I struck you,But in My favor
        I have had mercy on you."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Therefore your gates shall be open continually;They shall not be shut
        day or night,That men may bring to you the wealth of the Gentiles,And their
        kings in procession.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: For the nation and kingdom which will not serve you shall perish,And
        those nations shall be utterly ruined.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CThe glory of Lebanon shall come to you,The cypress, the pine,
        and the box tree together,To beautify the place of My sanctuary;And I will
        make the place of My feet glorious."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Also the sons of those who afflicted youShall come bowing to you,And
        all those who despised you shall fall prostrate at the soles of your feet;And
        they shall call you The City of the Lord,Zion of the Holy One of Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CWhereas you have been forsaken and hated,So that no one went
        through you,I will make you an eternal excellence,A joy of many generations."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: You shall drink the milk of the Gentiles,And milk the breast of kings;You
        shall know that I, the Lord, am your SaviorAnd your Redeemer, the Mighty
        One of Jacob.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CInstead of bronze I will bring gold,Instead of iron I will
        bring silver,Instead of wood, bronze,And instead of stones, iron.I will also
        make your officers peace,And your magistrates righteousness."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: God the Glory of His People'
      title: God the Glory of His People
      number: 18
      content: Violence shall no longer be heard in your land,Neither wasting nor
        destruction within your borders;But you shall call your walls Salvation,And
        your gates Praise.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CThe sun shall no longer be your light by day,Nor for brightness
        shall the moon give light to you;But the Lord will be to you an everlasting
        light,And your God your glory."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Your sun shall no longer go down,Nor shall your moon withdraw itself;For
        the Lord will be your everlasting light,And the days of your mourning shall
        be ended.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Also your people shall all be righteous;They shall inherit the land
        forever,The branch of My planting,The work of My hands,That I may be glorified.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "A little one shall become a thousand,And a small one a strong nation.I,
        the Lord, will hasten it in its time.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Good News of Salvation'
      title: The Good News of Salvation
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CThe Spirit of the Lord God  is upon Me,Because the Lord  has
        anointed MeTo preach good tidings to the poor;He has sent Me to heal the
        brokenhearted,To proclaim liberty to the captives,And the opening of the
        prison to those  who  are bound;"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: To proclaim the acceptable year of the Lord,And the day of vengeance
        of our God;To comfort all who mourn,
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "To console those who mourn in Zion,To give them beauty for ashes,The
        oil of joy for mourning,The garment of praise for the spirit of heaviness;That
        they may be called trees of righteousness,The planting of the Lord, that
        He may be glorified.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: And they shall rebuild the old ruins,They shall raise up the former
        desolations,And they shall repair the ruined cities,The desolations of many
        generations.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Strangers shall stand and feed your flocks,And the sons of the foreignerShall 
        be your plowmen and your vinedressers.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: But you shall be named the priests of the Lord,They shall call you
        the servants of our God.You shall eat the riches of the Gentiles,And in their
        glory you shall boast.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Instead of your shame you  shall  have double honor,And instead  of
        confusion they shall rejoice in their portion.Therefore in their land they
        shall possess double;Everlasting joy shall be theirs.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CFor I, the Lord, love justice;I hate robbery for burnt offering;I
        will direct their work in truth,And will make with them an everlasting covenant."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Their descendants shall be known among the Gentiles,And their offspring
        among the people.All who see them shall acknowledge them,That they are the
        posterity whom the Lord has blessed.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: I will greatly rejoice in the Lord,My soul shall be joyful in my God;For
        He has clothed me with the garments of salvation,He has covered me with the
        robe of righteousness,As a bridegroom decks himself with ornaments,And as
        a bride adorns herself with her jewels.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: For as the earth brings forth its bud,As the garden causes the things
        that are sown in it to spring forth,So the Lord God will cause righteousness
        and praise to spring forth before all the nations.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Assurance of Zion\u2019s Salvation"
      title: "Assurance of Zion\u2019s Salvation"
      number: 1
      content: "For Zion\u2019s sake I will not hold My peace,And for Jerusalem\u2019s
        sake I will not rest,Until her righteousness goes forth as brightness,And
        her salvation as a lamp that burns."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: The Gentiles shall see your righteousness,And all kings your glory.You
        shall be called by a new name,Which the mouth of the Lord will name.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: You shall also be a crown of gloryIn the hand of the Lord,And a royal
        diademIn the hand of your God.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: You shall no longer be termed Forsaken,Nor shall your land any more
        be termed Desolate;But you shall be called Hephzibah, and your land Beulah;For
        the Lord delights in you,And your land shall be married.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: For as a young man marries a virgin,So shall your sons marry you;And
        as the bridegroom rejoices over the bride,So shall your God rejoice over
        you.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: I have set watchmen on your walls, O Jerusalem;They shall never hold
        their peace day or night.You who make mention of the Lord, do not keep silent,
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: And give Him no rest till He establishesAnd till He makes Jerusalem
        a praise in the earth.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The Lord has sworn by His right handAnd by the arm of His strength:\u201CSurely
        I will no longer give your grainAs food for your enemies;And the sons of
        the foreigner shall not drink your new wine,For which you have labored."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But those who have gathered it shall eat it,And praise the Lord;Those
        who have brought it together shall drink it in My holy courts.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Go through,Go through the gates!Prepare the way for the people;Build
        up,Build up the highway!Take out the stones,Lift up a banner for the peoples!
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Indeed the Lord has proclaimedTo the end of the world:\u201CSay to
        the daughter of Zion,\u2018Surely your salvation is coming;Behold, His reward
        is with Him,And His work before Him.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: And they shall call them The Holy People,The Redeemed of the Lord;And
        you shall be called Sought Out,A City Not Forsaken.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Lord in Judgment and Salvation'
      title: The Lord in Judgment and Salvation
      number: 1
      content: "Who is this who comes from Edom,With dyed garments from Bozrah,This
        One  who  is glorious in His apparel,Traveling in the greatness of His strength?\u2014\u201CI
        who speak in righteousness, mighty to save.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Why is Your apparel red,And Your garments like one who treads in the
        winepress?
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CI have trodden the winepress alone,And from the peoples no
        one was with Me.For I have trodden them in My anger,And trampled them in
        My fury;Their blood is sprinkled upon My garments,And I have stained all
        My robes."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: For the day of vengeance is in My heart,And the year of My redeemed
        has come.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: I looked, but there  was no one to help,And I wonderedThat there 
        was no one to uphold;Therefore My own arm brought salvation for Me;And My
        own fury, it sustained Me.
      comments: []
    - name: "6: God\u2019s Mercy Remembered"
      title: "God\u2019s Mercy Remembered"
      number: 6
      content: "I have trodden down the peoples in My anger,Made them drunk in My
        fury,And brought down their strength to the earth.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: I will mention the lovingkindnesses of the LordAnd the praises of
        the Lord,According to all that the Lord has bestowed on us,And the great
        goodness toward the house of Israel,Which He has bestowed on them according
        to His mercies,According to the multitude of His lovingkindnesses.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "For He said, \u201CSurely they are My people,Children who will not
        lie.\u201DSo He became their Savior."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: In all their affliction He was afflicted,And the Angel of His Presence
        saved them;In His love and in His pity He redeemed them;And He bore them
        and carried themAll the days of old.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: But they rebelled and grieved His Holy Spirit;So He turned Himself
        against them as an enemy,And He fought against them.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then he remembered the days of old,Moses and his people, saying:\u201CWhere
        is He who brought them up out of the seaWith the shepherd of His flock?Where
        is He who put His Holy Spirit within them,"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Who led them by the right hand of Moses,With His glorious arm,Dividing
        the water before themTo make for Himself an everlasting name,
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Who led them through the deep,As a horse in the wilderness,That they
        might not stumble?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: A Prayer of Penitence'
      title: A Prayer of Penitence
      number: 14
      content: As a beast goes down into the valley,And the Spirit of the Lord causes
        him to rest,So You lead Your people,To make Yourself a glorious name.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Look down from heaven,And see from Your habitation, holy and glorious.Where
        are Your zeal and Your strength,The yearning of Your heart and Your mercies
        toward me?Are they restrained?
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Doubtless You are our Father,Though Abraham was ignorant of us,And
        Israel does not acknowledge us.You, O Lord, are our Father;Our Redeemer from
        Everlasting is Your name.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "O Lord, why have You made us stray from Your ways,And hardened our
        heart from Your fear?Return for Your servants\u2019 sake,The tribes of Your
        inheritance."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Your holy people have possessed it but a little while;Our adversaries
        have trodden down Your sanctuary.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: We have become like those of old, over whom You never ruled,Those
        who were never called by Your name.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "Oh, that You would rend the heavens!That You would come down!That
        the mountains might shake at Your presence\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "As fire burns brushwood,As fire causes water to boil\u2014To make
        Your name known to Your adversaries,That the nations may tremble at Your
        presence!"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: When You did awesome things for  which we did not look,You came down,The
        mountains shook at Your presence.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: For since the beginning of the worldMen have not heard nor perceived
        by the ear,Nor has the eye seen any God besides You,Who acts for the one
        who waits for Him.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "You meet him who rejoices and does righteousness,Who remembers You
        in Your ways.You are indeed angry, for we have sinned\u2014In these ways
        we continue;And we need to be saved."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: But we are all like an unclean thing,And all our righteousnesses are
        like filthy rags;We all fade as a leaf,And our iniquities, like the wind,Have
        taken us away.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: And there  is no one who calls on Your name,Who stirs himself up to
        take hold of You;For You have hidden Your face from us,And have consumed
        us because of our iniquities.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: But now, O Lord,You are our Father;We are the clay, and You our potter;And
        all we are the work of Your hand.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Do not be furious, O Lord,Nor remember iniquity forever;Indeed, please
        look\u2014we all are Your people!"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Your holy cities are a wilderness,Zion is a wilderness,Jerusalem a
        desolation.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Our holy and beautiful temple,Where our fathers praised You,Is burned
        up with fire;And all our pleasant things are laid waste.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Will You restrain Yourself because of these things, O Lord?Will You
        hold Your peace, and afflict us very severely?
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The Righteousness of God\u2019s Judgment"
      title: "The Righteousness of God\u2019s Judgment"
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CI was sought by those  who did not ask for  Me;I was found
        by those  who did not seek Me.I said, \u2018Here I am, here I am,\u2019To
        a nation that  was not called by My name."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: I have stretched out My hands all day long to a rebellious people,Who
        walk in a way that  is not good,According to their own thoughts;
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: A people who provoke Me to anger continually to My face;Who sacrifice
        in gardens,And burn incense on altars of brick;
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Who sit among the graves,And spend the night in the tombs;Who eat
        swine\u2019s flesh,And the broth of abominable things is in their vessels;"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Who say, \u2018Keep to yourself,Do not come near me,For I am holier
        than you!\u2019These are smoke in My nostrils,A fire that burns all the day."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CBehold, it  is written before Me:I will not keep silence, but
        will repay\u2014Even repay into their bosom\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Your iniquities and the iniquities of your fathers together,\u201DSays
        the Lord,\u201CWho have burned incense on the mountainsAnd blasphemed Me
        on the hills;Therefore I will measure their former work into their bosom.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Thus says the Lord:\u201CAs the new wine is found in the cluster,And
        one says, \u2018Do not destroy it,For a blessing is in it,\u2019So will I
        do for My servants\u2019 sake,That I may not destroy them all."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: I will bring forth descendants from Jacob,And from Judah an heir of
        My mountains;My elect shall inherit it,And My servants shall dwell there.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Sharon shall be a fold of flocks,And the Valley of Achor a place for
        herds to lie down,For My people who have sought Me.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CBut you are those who forsake the Lord,Who forget My holy mountain,Who
        prepare a table for Gad,And who furnish a drink offering for Meni."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Therefore I will number you for the sword,And you shall all bow down
        to the slaughter;Because, when I called, you did not answer;When I spoke,
        you did not hear,But did evil before My eyes,And chose that in which I do
        not delight.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord God:\u201CBehold, My servants shall
        eat,But you shall be hungry;Behold, My servants shall drink,But you shall
        be thirsty;Behold, My servants shall rejoice,But you shall be ashamed;"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Behold, My servants shall sing for joy of heart,But you shall cry
        for sorrow of heart,And wail for grief of spirit.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: You shall leave your name as a curse to My chosen;For the Lord God
        will slay you,And call His servants by another name;
      comments: []
    - name: '16: The Glorious New Creation'
      title: The Glorious New Creation
      number: 16
      content: So that he who blesses himself in the earthShall bless himself in
        the God of truth;And he who swears in the earthShall swear by the God of
        truth;Because the former troubles are forgotten,And because they are hidden
        from My eyes.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CFor behold, I create new heavens and a new earth;And the former
        shall not be remembered or come to mind."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: But be glad and rejoice forever in what I create;For behold, I create
        Jerusalem as a rejoicing,And her people a joy.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: I will rejoice in Jerusalem,And joy in My people;The voice of weeping
        shall no longer be heard in her,Nor the voice of crying.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CNo more shall an infant from there live  but  a  few days,Nor
        an old man who has not fulfilled his days;For the child shall die one hundred
        years old,But the sinner being one hundred years old shall be accursed."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: They shall build houses and inhabit them;They shall plant vineyards
        and eat their fruit.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: They shall not build and another inhabit;They shall not plant and
        another eat;For as the days of a tree, so  shall  be the days of My people,And
        My elect shall long enjoy the work of their hands.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: They shall not labor in vain,Nor bring forth children for trouble;For
        they shall  be the descendants of the blessed of the Lord,And their offspring
        with them.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CIt shall come to passThat before they call, I will answer;And
        while they are still speaking, I will hear."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "The wolf and the lamb shall feed together,The lion shall eat straw
        like the ox,And dust shall  be the serpent\u2019s food.They shall not hurt
        nor destroy in all My holy mountain,\u201DSays the Lord."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: True Worship and False'
      title: True Worship and False
      number: 1
      content: "Thus says the Lord:\u201CHeaven is My throne,And earth is My footstool.Where
        is the house that you will build Me?And where is the place of My rest?"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "For all those things My hand has made,And all those things exist,\u201DSays
        the Lord.\u201CBut on this one will I look:On him  who  is poor and of a
        contrite spirit,And who trembles at My word."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CHe who kills a bull is  as  if he slays a man;He who sacrifices
        a lamb, as  if he breaks a dog\u2019s neck;He who offers a grain offering,
        as  if  he  offers swine\u2019s blood;He who burns incense, as  if he blesses
        an idol.Just as they have chosen their own ways,And their soul delights in
        their abominations,"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: The Lord Vindicates Zion'
      title: The Lord Vindicates Zion
      number: 4
      content: "So will I choose their delusions,And bring their fears on them;Because,
        when I called, no one answered,When I spoke they did not hear;But they did
        evil before My eyes,And chose that in which I do not delight.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Hear the word of the Lord,You who tremble at His word:\u201CYour
        brethren who hated you,Who cast you out for My name\u2019s sake, said,\u2018Let
        the Lord be glorified,That we may see your joy.\u2019But they shall be ashamed.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: The sound of noise from the city!A voice from the temple!The voice
        of the Lord,Who fully repays His enemies!
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CBefore she was in labor, she gave birth;Before her pain came,She
        delivered a male child."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Who has heard such a thing?Who has seen such things?Shall the earth
        be made to give birth in one day?Or shall a nation be born at once?For as
        soon as Zion was in labor,She gave birth to her children.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Shall I bring to the time of birth, and not cause delivery?\u201D
        says the Lord.\u201CShall I who cause delivery shut up the  womb?\u201D says
        your God."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CRejoice with Jerusalem,And be glad with her, all you who love
        her;Rejoice for joy with her, all you who mourn for her;"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "That you may feed and be satisfiedWith the consolation of her bosom,That
        you may drink deeply and be delightedWith the abundance of her glory.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "For thus says the Lord:\u201CBehold, I will extend peace to her like
        a river,And the glory of the Gentiles like a flowing stream.Then you shall
        feed;On her sides shall you be carried,And be dandled on her knees."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: The Reign and Indignation of God'
      title: The Reign and Indignation of God
      number: 13
      content: "As one whom his mother comforts,So I will comfort you;And you shall
        be comforted in Jerusalem.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: When you see this, your heart shall rejoice,And your bones shall flourish
        like grass;The hand of the Lord shall be known to His servants,And His indignation
        to His enemies.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: For behold, the Lord will come with fireAnd with His chariots, like
        a whirlwind,To render His anger with fury,And His rebuke with flames of fire.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: For by fire and by His swordThe Lord will judge all flesh;And the
        slain of the Lord shall be many.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CThose who sanctify themselves and purify themselves,To  go
        to the gardensAfter an idol in the midst,Eating swine\u2019s flesh and the
        abomination and the mouse,Shall be consumed together,\u201D says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CFor I know their works and their thoughts. It shall be that
        I will gather all nations and tongues; and they shall come and see My glory. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'I will set a sign among them; and those among them who escape I will
        send to the nations: to Tarshish and Pul and Lud, who draw the bow, and Tubal
        and Javan, to the coastlands afar off who have not heard My fame nor seen
        My glory. And they shall declare My glory among the Gentiles. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then they shall bring all your brethren for an offering to the Lord
        out of all nations, on horses and in chariots and in litters, on mules and
        on camels, to My holy mountain Jerusalem,\u201D says the Lord, \u201Cas the
        children of Israel bring an offering in a clean vessel into the house of
        the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And I will also take some of them for priests and Levites,\u201D
        says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CFor as the new heavens and the new earthWhich I will make shall
        remain before Me,\u201D says the Lord,\u201CSo shall your descendants and
        your name remain."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And it shall come to passThat from one New Moon to another,And from
        one Sabbath to another,All flesh shall come to worship before Me,\u201D says
        the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CAnd they shall go forth and lookUpon the corpses of the menWho
        have transgressed against Me.For their worm does not die,And their fire is
        not quenched.They shall be an abhorrence to all flesh.\u201D"
      comments: []
